2016 Bursa bombing: A suicide bomber blew herself up in the Turkish city of Bursa, wounding 13 people in the Bursa's 14th century Grand Mosque, a historic symbol of the city that was the first capital of the Ottoman Empire.
An army ranger has been killed and five others wounded in a roadside bomb attack Yala Province, while the military personnel were on patrol.
Five people were killed in a gun and grenade attack in a district of Burundi's capital which is stronghold of opposition to president Pierre Nkurunziza.
Three people died and three others were injured during an armed attack against a position of the Armed Forces of the Democratic Republic of the Congo in North Kivu.
Standardized-Location: Masisi, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: One police officer was killed and two others were wounded in an outlawed Kurdistan Workers' Party bomb attack in the Varto district. PKK militants detonated an explosive placed on the road during the passing of an armored police vehicle.

Militants used car bombs, killing 11 members of the security forces and wounding 12 others. Militants also attacked security forces near Makhoul, killing three police officers and wounding two others.
A Hindu tailor was killed in central Bangladesh, by several men on a motorcycle. The crime was quickly claimed by the organization Islamic State through the news agency of the terrorist group.

April 2016 Baghdad bombing: A suicide bomber driving a car killed at least 38 people and wounded 86 others on April 30 in an attack claimed by Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) on a group of Shi'ite Muslim pilgrims in a southeastern suburb of Baghdad, Iraqi police sources said. A second explosion near a Shi'ite militia checkpoint in the capital's Dora district killed two and wounded three others, police sources said. There was no immediate claim of responsibility for that blast.
May 2016 Gaziantep bombing: Two policeman was killed and twenty-two others (four being civilians) were wounded after a car bomb exploded out a police headquarters in Gaziantep.
Seven people were wounded when three rockets fired from an area in Syria controlled by Islamic State jihadists crashed into the centre of Kilis.
several children are among over three dozen dead after two suicide car bombs blast go off in different areas.
twenty-two defenders of a small town are killed during an al-shabaab attack that started out with a suicide bomber.
four teenagers are beheaded by the Islamic state
A suicide bomber attacked the security chief's motorcade in the southern port city, killing five of his bodyguards.

Militant group Al-Shabaab attacked and recaptured a town in Somalia's Middle Shebelle region killing 22 Somali soldiers. The militants used a suicide car bomb in the assault and seized at least three military vehicles.
2016 Samawa bombing
Sixteen Shiite pilgrims were killed and 43 others wounded in a suicide car bomb explosion in Baghdad.
One soldier was killed and 23 people were injured in a suicide car bomb against the security forces in Diyarbakır.
Palestinian man stabbed an old Jewish man at the Lions' Gate in the Old City of Jerusalem. The assailant fled the scene and was later caught and admitted he carried out the attack.
Three Israelis were wounded in a car-ramming attack near Dolev settlement in the West Bank. The driver of the vehicle was shot and killed.
Two soldiers were killed when outlawed PKK attacked a military station zone in the Şemdinli district of the southeastern province of Hakkâri Province.
At least 38 people were killed by suspected rebels ADF in the city of Beni in North Kivu.
Standardized-Location: Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: A U.S. Navy SEAL was killed in Iraq after Islamic State attacked a Peshmerga base. Roughly 100 ISIL fighters have break through a checkpoint at the frontline and drove 3 to 5 kilometers to the Peshmerga base. The U.S. responded with F-15's and drones that dropped more than 20 bombs.
Four children are among fifteen civilians murdered by Jabhat al-Nusra.
PKK used a car laden with explosives to attack a gendarmerie station in Turkey's Mardin. Initial reports from the scene said that 1 soldier has died and 10 others have been wounded.

At least 12 people have been killed and 45 injured, some of them seriously, in twin suicide blasts in the Syrian city of Homs, a car and a motorcycle exploded in the Mukharram al-Fawqani area in the eastern part of the city.
A child died and eight other people were injured after rockets fired from the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant-controlled territory in Syria hit the south-central Turkish Kilis province
Five Libyan soldiers have been killed in an ISIL attack in the northwestern city of Misrata.
An Afghan official said a roadside bombing killed five civilians and wounded five others in a remote northwestern province.
Five people were killed and 11 wounded on Friday when shells hit a political rally in the centre of Libya's second city Benghazi.
Seven people were killed and more than 15 wounded by a bomb in the Yemeni city Ma'rib, east of the capital Sana'a.
Eight people were injured by a grenade explosion, in the north of Bujumbura,
At least four people were killed by suspected rebels ADF in the city of Biane.
Gunmen wearing Afghan military uniforms shot dead two Romanian soldiers in the country's south on Saturday, officials said,
A chlorine gas rocket attack killed 3 and injured hundreds.
The remains of over 160 people were found in over 50 mass graves after ISIS committed a mass execution and genocide.
At least four children lost their lives and another sustained injuries in a powerful bomb explosion in a rural area in Afghanistan's southern province of Zabul.
A grenade was thrown in a small market. Its explosion killed two saleswoman and injured twelve others
Four gunmen killed eight police officers dressed in plainclothes south of Cairo on Sunday, authorities said.
One person was killed and five others injuredin the explosion of a grenade in a bar, in the center of Bujumbura.
At least one policeman was killed and four wounded in a terrorist attack in Grozny. A terrorist blew himself up, another was killed by security forces.
A car bomb claimed by ISIL exploded in the eastern Iraqi city of Baquba. It killed at least 16 civilians and wounded 54 others outside of a bakery not far from the city center.
ISIL branch in the Philippines claimed responsibility on Monday for a terror attack against a military position on Basilan Island, killing one soldier and injuring other.
At least 12 people were injured in a hand grenade attack in Pakistan's southern port city of Karachi on Sunday.
A suicide car bomb targeting Mogadishu's traffic police headquarters killed between 2 and 4. Al-Shabaab claims responsibility.

Three people were killed in a bar in Maramvya, Burambi district of Rumonge province, 70 km south of the Burundian capital Bujumbura. Two of the victims were retired soldiers. Another man was seriously injured in the shooting.
A prominent Pakistani anti-militant activist was killed by four armed men, while his friend was injured.
Two elderly women were injured in an stabbing attack in Jerusalem's Armon HaNatziv neighborhood.
Sufi Muslim leader Mohammad Shahidullah was found dead in a suspected attack by militants.
Two Israeli soldiers were wounded by an explosive device at the crossing of Hizma near Ramallah in the West Bank.
A provincial official says a bomb has exploded in the parking area of a state-run university in southwestern Pakistan, killing two police officers and wounding five people.
May 2016 Diyarbakır bombing: At least three are killed in a car bomb targeting a Turkish police vehicle in Diyarbakır, Turkey.
A suicide car bombing in an eastern Afghan region bordering Pakistan killed at least 11 people.

One Ukrainian serviceman was killed and three others wounded in action in the Donbass region on 10 May. All the casualties were caused by explosions of explosive devices. Two civilians, employees of a thermal power station, were injured by explosion of a grenade launcher's ammunition that was hidden underground.

Perpetrator: Al-Qaeda (suspected) and Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant
Details: At least 13 soldiers were killed in three attacks on army bases in the southern Yemen city of Mukalla, military sources said. The attacks came hours before Yemen PM Ahmed Obeid bin Daghr was due to arrive in Mukalla for a visit.

Perpetrator: Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant

Details: Nigerian army says troops from its 7 Division Garrison, intercepted a Boko Haram terrorist detonating a suicide bomb in Sulaimanti community, in the outskirts of Maiduguri, Borno State.
Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant buried 45 men alive in Qayyarah vicinity in Nineveh Governorate.
A suicide bomber who was stopped from entering a government compound killed at least six people, including two police officers, in the northeastern Nigerian city of Maiduguri.
AQAP militants kill at least 13 Yemeni government troops near the city of Mukalla.

Zara'a massacre: 42 confirmed civilians and seven National Defence Forces militiamen were killed in the militant attack on the Alawite village of Zara'a, Hama Governorate. Around 70 other civilians, including women and children were kidnapped and taken to Al-Rastan. On 24 May 2016, the Syrian Red Crescent convinced the militants to hand over 49 victim bodies. They were transported by the Syrian Army to the Homs Military Hospital for identification the next day.
Real Madrid Fan Club massacre: At least 16 Real Madrid fans were killed and at least 30 injured after ISIS attacked their clubhouse.
Seven civilians including two children were killed in rebel shelling of government-held western sectors.
6 soldiers were killed during clash with PKK fighters near a military base
ISIL militants attacked a hospital in the eastern Syrian city of Deir ez-Zor Saturday, killing 20 pro-government fighters.
Police in Bangladesh said a 75-year-old Buddhist monk has been hacked to death in the south-eastern district of Bandarban.
At least two people are killed and 12 injured after a suicide bomb attack on a police training center in Helmand Province.
Militants killed two police in Russia's Dagestan, ISIL claimed responsibility.
2016 Iraq Gas Plant attack: Suicide bomb attacks in a state owned cooking gas plant in Taji north of Baghdad kill at least 14 people.
May 2016 Yemen police bombings: A suicide bombing killed at least 47 and injured at least 60 in the southern city of Mukalla. Some sources say 40 were killed.

Assailants attacked a police station in Les Cayes, Sud, Haiti. At least seven people, including a police officer and six assailants were killed in the attack. No group claimed responsibility for the incident.
17 May 2016 Baghdad bombings: A series of eight attacks in Baghdad killed numerous people and wounded more.

One male civilian was killed and another injured when a tractor they were driving on hit an unidentified explosive device in Pavlopil, Donetsk Oblast. The incident in Pavlopil was the fifth incident of similar kind since the beginning of 2016.
Twin bombings kill a police officer and wound nine people in Peshawar, Pakistan.
Five Chadian peacekeepers were killed and three others wounded in attack on convoy. They hit a landmine and then came under sustained gunfire. Ansar Dine claimed the attack.
A chemistry student put a bomb on a bus. The bus driver led the explosive charge to the bus stop. No one died in the attack.
A booby-trapped house went off on a force belonging to the Iraqi army in the village of al-Refai in the area of Arab Jabour, south of Baghdad, resulting in the injury of three soldiers.

Eleven members of a family were killed when their car hit a roadside mine in northern Afghanistan. Five children, two women and four men were killed, and three other children were injured in the explosion.

Three people were killed at a mosque in north-west Tanzania in what police have described as a "terrorist-style attack". More than a dozen attackers carrying machetes and axes attacked. The police made three arrests. The mosque's imam was among the dead.

Gang groups conducted a heavy aggression with mortars and hell cannons targeting the Sheikh Maqsoud neighborhood on May 20. The attack that targeted civilian areas left 5 civilians including a child dead and 3 others wounded.
A suicide bomber attacks a NATO convoy in Parwan province, wounding two civilians.
Six police members are killed in an insider attack in Uruzgan province.
A homeopathic doctor is hacked to death in Bangladesh. Islamic State of Iraq and Syria claim responsibility.
The driver of a vehicle died when he blew himself up at an al-Hashd al-Shaabi checkpoint in Suliman Bek. Two men working at the checkpoint were injured.
One volunteer soldier was killed and five others were wounded in an explosion when on patrol near al-Yusufiyah, south of Baghdad.
Two members of ISIS wearing explosive belts were killed by the army's 7th brigade and tribal fighters in the al-Sekak area.
At least six people were killed and 15 injured in Qamishli. A car bomb reportedly exploded near Kurdish self-defense forces' checkpoint.
A "suicide operation" killed more than a dozen Kurdish security personnel but issued no claim.
At least eight people were killed and 20 more injured in a suicide bombing at a restaurant in Qamishli.
Two traffic wardens were killed after being gunned down by two men.
Rebels ambush and kill six Indian paramilitary soldiers in the state of Manipur, near the northeastern border with Myanmar.
Three policemen are killed in Srinagar, India. Hizbul Mujahideen claims responsibility.

23 May 2016 Yemen bombings:At least 45 army recruits are killed and 60 others injured in a suicide car bomb attack in Aden, Yemen. The Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant group claims responsibility.

23 May 2016 Syrian bombings: Nearly 150 people are killed and at least 200 wounded in a series of car bomb and suicide attacks in the Syrian cities of Jableh and Tartus in government-controlled territory that hosts Russian military bases. The Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant claims responsibility.
At least six Turkish soldiers are killed and four others are wounded in a PKK attack in Turkey's eastern Van Province.
Seven Ukrainian servicemen are killed in suspected attacks by pro-Russian rebels
At least 2 killed and at least twi injured in an attack near Sanaa University.
An IED kills two and injures 6 near a restaurant southeast of Baghdad.
One person dead and seven injured after an explosive device went off near a popular market south of Baghdad.
Two were killed and four were injured after a planted roadside bomb went off.
A suicide bomber targeted Turkish Peshmerga forces, but was unsuccessful and was killed.
A bomb went off in southern Baghdad, killing one and injuring seven others.
A Taliban suicide bomber targeted employees on a bus, killing 11. The attack was revenge for the killing of six prisoners in Kabul, and it came soon after the death of Mullah Akhtar Mansour
Gunmen killed two people, including a police chief. One other person was wounded.
Retired army Colonel Lucien Rufyiri was killed and his son wounded in a shooting.
An elderly Hindu trader was stabbed to death in another in a series of killings claimed by ISIS.
ISIS executed 8 of its own fighters while the Patriotic Union of Kurdistan attacked and killed five ISIS members.
A bomb exploded during a police patrol, killing 2 police and injuring four others. The vehicle was damaged.
ISIS launched three Katyusha rockets into a village. No human casualties have been so far reported.
A bomb exploded near shops, killing 1 and wounding 7.
A member of al-Hashd al-Shaabi was wounded by an IED explosion.
An Ahmadi man was shot dead by two unknown gunmen, while his friend was injured.
An explosive device went off near a café, killing 2 and injuring 8.
An explosive device went off on the side of a road, injuring the driver of a civilian vehicle. No deaths so far have been reported.
Four Shia men were gunned down in Saudabad. One man was a Muttahida Qaumi Movement activist, and another man was tortured before he was killed.

A French military in a "serious condition" after being attacked with knives in Saint-Julien-du-Puy (Tarn). The military was approached by two men who "have criticized the French bombing in Syria." He was then beaten with fists and beaten cutter.
Michael Phelemebe, an ANC branch deputy chairperson was shot four times in his house in Mbombela. He succumbed to his wounds in the hospital.
ISIS shelled civilians attempting to escape from southern Fallujah, killing 2 and injuring 20.
Two people were killed and seven injured during a bombing at a market in northern Baghdad.
Two people were killed and eight injured after an explosive device went off near a cafe in northern Baghdad.
A suicide bomber killed 7 and injured 35 in a casino in al-Moalmeen.

A suicide bomber failed to break into a casino and was shot by a policeman. The policeman's bullet hit the bomb, causing it to explode, killing 3 and injuring 10 civilians, the second attack in the city in under one day.
2 people were killed and 4 injured after a bomb exploded on a car in southern Baghdad. All of the victims were civilian members of al-Hashed al-Shaabi.
1 person was killed and 5 injured in a bombing near a parking garage.
ISIS attacked the city, killing 25 and injuring 5. Civilians and security forces were killed. The number of deaths and injuries has been disputed.

Real Madrid Fan Club massacre: At least 12 Real Madrid fans were killed and more injured when watching the 2016 UEFA Champions League Final. The attacks are preceded by another attack earlier in the month on a different club that killed at least 16.
A tricycle taxi triggered an old IED, killing 4 civilians and one soldier who died of his injuries. Two were wounded.
Gunmen ambushed UN peacekeepers near Sévaré town. Five Togolese peacekeepers were killed and another was injured in the ambush.
A Chinese citizen is among the 3 injured in a roadside bombing.
A chlorine gas rocket attack injured 35 people. Some sources state that 2 died.
One person was killed and eight injured after an explosive device went off near a café.
2 civilians were injured after a moving vehicle blew up from a bomb that was attached on the underside. No deaths so far reported.

Four civilians were killed and nineteen people, including 5 policemen, were wounded when a roadside bomb that had been placed in a street sewer was detonated when a police car passed. PKK has been blamed for the attack.
Suspected PKK militants detonated a roadside bomb in the city of Van as an armored vehicle passed. Two policemen were killed and a third was wounded.
An Islamic militant group executed 2 mill workers during an attack, and 56 of them were killed.
2 volunteer members of al-Hashed al-Sha’bi were killed and 3 injured in a bombing.
6 people were killed and 13 injured during an explosion near a market.
1 person was killed and 9 injured during an explosion near a shop.
1 person was killed and 6 injured during an explosion near a medical center.
3 suicide bombers attempted an unsuccessful attack and were killed by security forces.
ISIS attacked the North Gas Company with four Katyusha rockets. No deaths have been so far reported.
One civilian was killed and 2 injured in a roadside bombing that was aimed at civilians.
2 people were killed and 8 injured in a bombing near a market.
4 people were killed and 13 injured in a suicide bombing, many suffered serious injuries. Most of the victims were al-Hashed al-Shaabi members. The death toll is expected to increase.
2 people were killed and 9 injured in a bombing at a café.
1 people was killed and 2 injured after a sniper shot at a police checkpoint.

A border police post located at Intangom, 4 km from the Malian border in the province of Oudalan was attacked by unidentified individuals. During the attack, three policemen were killed and property damaged.

Kunduz-Takhar highway hostage crisis: The Taliban executed at least 17 people after kidnapping around 220 people on buses and in cars at a fake checkpoint on the Kunduz-Takhar highway. 6 people were killed by Afghan forces when the attempted to flee the scene. Around 20 hostages have been moved to Char Dara District.
In the evening, a bomb exploded in the southeast of Baghdad in al-Za'faraniya outside a medical center. twenty-one people where killed and eight others were wounded.
ten libyans are taken out by two isis suicide bombers.
three young men are forced to there knees and shot in the back of the head by the islamic state.
thirteen people are executed for refusing to join the islamic state.

June 2016 Mogadishu attack: A suicide bomber detonated a car bomb outside the Ambassador Hotel in Mogadishu after which two gunmen opened fire on the hotel and took hostages before being killed by police. 16 people were killed and several dozen more wounded. Al-Shabaab claimed responsibility.
2 people were killed and 9 injured after a bombing near a playground.
13 Iraqi Army weapons experts and officers were executed by ISIS for refusing to work with them.
1 person was killed and 9 injured after a bombing near shops.
4 suicide bombers were killed before they could attack. No other deaths reported yet.
The Taliban stormed a court building, killing 9 and injuring 13. A firefight broke out between them and the police, and 4 attackers were killed.

Four UN Mali mission staff were killed in two attack. A Chinese peacekeeper was killed-the first Chinese peacekeeper to be killed in the north. Three other Chinese peacekeepers were injured in the first attack. In the second attack two security guards and an international expert was killed, one was French and the other two are from Mali. AQIM claimed the attack.
1 person was killed and 1 injured after a gunmen shot at a civilian house.
five people are reportedly killed when a suicide bomber strikes a rival mosque.
muslim youths behead a christian women for insulting muhammad after an argument over religion.
1 person was killed and 9 injured after a bombing near a market.
A woman is among three aid workers murder by religious extremists.
An Islamist break into a policeman's house and murder him in front of his wife and children.
25 rockets and artillery shells were fired onto Qasbat Bashir, wounding three member of al-Hashed al-Turkmani.
A volunteer member of al-Hashed al-Sha'bi was killed by a roadside bomb.
At least 18 civilians were killed and at least 35 injured after Katyusha rockets hit a market.
ISIS burned 19 Yezidi girls after they refused to have sex with their captives.
3 BSF members were killed and 11 injured, including civilians, after a terrorist attack. 5 more policemen were also killed.
2 people were killed and 10 injured after a bombing in Mahmudiya district.
Over 40 people were killed after shellings, and at least 14 attackers were killed.
1 person was killed and 3 injured after a bombing south of Baghdad.
A suicide bombing in a neighbourhood killed 2 and injured 9.
1 person was killed and 3 injured after an IED went off in the area of al-Mahmudiya.

At least 32 people were killed and 67 injured after hundreds of members of Boko Haram attacked the city of Bosso and area in Niger. Many places in the city were torched and shot at. There were also several deaths and injuries of the attacker's side.
A woman was stabbed to death by two men after allegedly insulting the Prophet Muhammad.
3 civilians were beheaded. They were charged with working with the Iraqi government and Peshmerga forces.

2016 Aktobe shootings: Over 20 suspected Islamists militants attacked a military facility and two firearm stores in Aktobe, Kazakhstan. The attacks killed a clerk, a military officer and a serviceman at a national guard facility. Another nine servicemen were wounded. The police launched a counter-terrorist operation in which it managed to kill four militants and detain seven but others escaped. The perpetrators are suspected of being radical Islamists.

A woman was shot, stabbed, and killed by three men in front of her son. The woman was the wife of a prominent policeman that is heading an investigation into the recent string of killings committed by Islamic extremists.
A 65-year-old Christian was murdered by Islamic State militants.
ISIS executed over 30 people on charges of spying after the killing of Abu Hayjaa al-Tunsi.
Several of civilians were shot and killed as they tried to escape ISIS controlled territories while swimming or taking a boat across the Euphrates River.
NPR reporter David Gilkey and his interpreter Zabihullah Tamanna were killed when their convoy was shelled.
1 person was killed and 3 injured after a bombing south of Baghdad.
3 people were killed and 7 injured after a bombing near a market.

3 Taliban gunmen stormed a courthouse, killing a chief prosecutor and at least 9 others, injuring 23. The three assailants were eventually killed by security forces. This is another in a series of attacks on judicial employees in Afghanistan.
Shir Wali Wardak, and Afghan MP, was killed by a bomb blast near his house. 11 others were injured.
400 soldiers were found dead, many with gun wounds. The soldiers were likely executed on an unknown date. They belonged to the army's 10th brigade.
ten fisherman are cut down by boko haram.
2 people were killed and 7 injured after a bombing near a café.
A local intelligence office near the capital Amman was attacked by Islamic militants. Three guards and two civilian intelligence office workers were killed.
ISIS executed 11 civilians for trying to flee ISIS controlled areas.
2 people were killed and 6 injured after an IED bombing near a market.
1 person was killed and 2 injured after an IED placed under a car carrying Baghdad Health Directorate employees exploded.
1 person was killed and 6 injured after a bombing near shops.
An attack by ISIS while wearing Iraqi army uniforms resulted in the deaths of 6 members and the injury of 4 of the Iraqi security forces. There was also another attack in the same proximity.
2 people were killed and 5 injured after an IED explosion.
2 people were killed and 11 injured after a bombing near a market.
An attack killed at least 7 people. A district intelligence chief and his deputy are among the dead. The attack comes after a gunbattle killed 4 militants.
A female journalist was killed by 3 gunmen near a college.
ISIS executed around 65 civilians and arrested around 90 in Mosul.
3 people were killed and 35 injured after a neighborhood attack, with members of al-Hashed among the casualties.
5 displaced civilians were killed after an IED bombing.
2 women were killed after 4 suicide bombers attacked the Haditha Asphalt Factory. 3 of the bombers were unsuccessful and were killed by police.
1 person was killed and 5 injured after an IED bombing near shops.
June 2016 Istanbul bombing: A bomb exploded on a police bus in the Vezneciler district of Istanbul
At least ten deaths and twenty-six injuries were reported in a car bomb attack on the first day of Ramadan.
Ananda Gopal Ganguly, a Hindu priest in Bangladesh, was attacked by melee, soon after three suspected Islamists were killed by police.
Part of: Internal conflict in Bangladesh, Attacks on secularists in Bangladesh (broad attacks)

Details: Over 20 were killed and over 40 injured after terrorist groups shelled the city.
June 2016 Midyat car bombing: a car bomb exploded in the Turkish town of Midyat. 5 people were killed and 30 others were injured.
5 were killed and over 50 injured after terrorist groups shelled the city using explosive gas balloons.

Perpetrator: Khalid al-Mahmara and Muhammad Ahmad Moussa Mahmara (inspired by the Islamic State)
Details: June 2016 Tel Aviv shooting: Two Palestinian gunmen opened fire in a Max Brenner restaurant in Tel Aviv killing four diners. Both perpetrators were arrested.
3 people were killed and 3 seriously wounded after a bombing in an orchard. The victims were members of al-Hashed al-Sha'bi.

Kunduz-Takhar highway hostage crisis: In a continuation of an ongoing event, 12 hostages were executed, and 42 more people were kidnapped. Four more people were also killed during the new kidnappings.
A man was executed because he was accused of being a "sorcerer" by the Islamic state.
A women was burnt alive for "eloping".
At least 12 people were killed and at least 32 wounded after a suicide bombing at a military headquarters, where New Zealand and Australia troops are located.
12 people were killed and at least 30 wounded after an attack. It is unknown whether or not attackers were killed.
At least 19 people were killed and over 50 injured after a car bombing in a market and neighbourhood.
1 person was killed and 3 wounded after a bombing that hit a family that was escaping ISIS.
A wave of attacks in Aleppo left at least 54 dead and 93 injured. The attacks included shellings that killed people and destroyed buildings.
A woman was stoned to death on charges of "adultery".
Nityaranjan Pande, a worker at a Hindu monastery in Bangladesh, was hacked to death by several people near the monastery. No immediate claim of responsibility was made but Islamists are suspected.
Part of: Internal conflict in Bangladesh, Attacks on secularists in Bangladesh (broad attacks)

Details: Three men were shot dead and another beheaded in the Bay region by Al-Shabaab for giving information to the United States which led to the death of the group leader.
3 people were killed and 11 wounded after a suicide bombing at a security checkpoint.
Two unity government soldiers were killed and seven were injured in clashes with ISIS fighters. 30 more were killed and 50 injured.
ISIS opened fire on fleeing civilians, killing at least 30.
At least 4 civilians were killed and around 60 injured after an IED bombing during prayer inside of a mosque. The death toll is likely higher than 4. An imam was among those killed.
1 person was killed and 8 wounded after a bombing near a market.
Two army officials had their houses stormed by gunmen and many of their family members killed.
ISIS executed 10 people on an unknown date, and their remains were only found today.
2 people were injured in an IED explosion.
ISIS attacked a police headquarters, killing a police chief and 4–13 others. 13 attackers were killed, 7 were injured, and 6 of the victims were also injured.

Two Kenyans were executed by Al-Shabaab for spying for Kenyan and western intelligence agencies. The victims were Jared Mukae Ombamba 31 from Eldoret and 22 years old Abdullah Faraj from Mombasa, Kenya.
At least 20 people were killed and 30 injured after two bombings near a Shia shrine in the capital.

ISIS massacred 40 civilians, and killed 6 more later on by shelling them. 35 were injured by the shelling, and an unknown number of people were injured by the shootings. ISIS was disguised as Kurdish fighters. 3 more were killed and 15 injured in a sniping attack.

A young man was brutally executed by the Taliban, who are reportedly trying to "mimic ISIS's methods". The execution process included things such as skinning alive and the victims eyes being gouged out. He was then thrown of a 10-storey cliff. A video was released by the Taliban showing the execution.

2016 Orlando nightclub shooting: 49 people were killed when an alleged lone-wolf gunman entered the Pulse gay nightclub. Hostages were taken and the perpetrator, Omar Mateen, was shot dead by local SWAT units in an attempt to storm the building. The FBI classified the attack as an act of "domestic terrorism" motivated by "Islamic leanings". An accomplice has been identified and is expected to be apprehended.
1 person was killed and 6 injured after a bombing near shops.
4 women were killed by 14 assailants after being dragged outside of their homes.

A small bomb exploded outside the Central Bank of Lebanon, injuring two people and shattering glass. No group claimed responsibility, but Hezbollah is suspected as the bank was involved in an American backed act that would attempt to stop the flow of money to Hezbollah.
Part of: Syrian Civil War spillover in Lebanon

Details: 3 suicide bombers killed 3 people and injured "dozens' after an attack on soldiers and medical workers at a hospital, causing damage. The death toll is disputed.

June 2016 Paris police stabbing: A man shouting "Islamist slogans" stabbed his neighbor, a 42-year-old police officer, to death before taking the officer's wife and son hostage. Police raided the house and killed the attacker and discovered the officer's wife dead but his son alive. ISIS claimed responsibitiy.
ISIS executed 19 people for fleeing from a battle.
Unknown militants shot dead an army officer.
A terrorist attack by ISIS was stopped by policeman, and an unknown number of assailants were killed.
1 person was killed and 2 injured after a sniping attack on a military checkpoint.
6 ISIS suicide bombers were killed, it is unknown if they killed anyone before they were killed by security forces.
A Canadian hostage was executed by a terrorist group connected to Al-Qaeda after he was abducted along with two others, the second execution of a Canadian in a short time period in the Philippines.
A video showed an ISIS militant executing his brother and another person for suspected spying. They were both shot dead.
At least 5 people were killed and 11 in injured after a suicide attack on an army base.
ISIS attacked security forces, and 40 of them were killed. The number of victims (if there are any) is unknown.
3 soldiers were injured by an explosion. A vehicle was also damaged.
2 people were killed and 9 injured after an IED bombing near a market.
1 person was killed and 7 injured after bombing in a street.
10 fishermen were killed by militants, and soon after 42 more were killed by Boko Haram at Lake Chad.

A double terrorist attack in India resulted in the death of a victim and a militant, and the injury of 9. The status of the second attacker is currently unknown. The attack sparked protests, as it was later revealed that two civilian victims were actually shot by Indian troops amid the chaos.
A soldier blew himself up with grenade, killing him and two other people as well as injuring four other people in the town of Ngozi in Ngozi Province.
2 people were killed and 7 injured after bombing near markets.
An employee of the Iraqi Justice Ministry was killed along with her son when unknown gunmen stormed her house.
1 person was killed and 5 injured after an IED bombing near a market.
2 people were killed and 3 injured after a suicide bombing near an army post on a major highway.

There is currently an ongoing clash between Iraqi policemen and ISIS militants, with a current unknown number of casualties. Airstrikes have been called in, and the clash has been described as "violent".

At least 4 females were killed and several abducted after many Boko Haram militants attacked a village. Some sources say the number of those kidnapped is four. Many houses were burned down and shot at. Vigilantes followed the attackers and rescued one of the kidnapped after a gun battle. A vigilante was injured.
A transgender man was stabbed by people who were described as Islamic state members.
9 people were killed and over 8 injured after a suicide bombing and another bombing.
2 people were killed and 3 injured after an IED bombing that targeted a police patrol, also damaging a vehicle.
3 people were killed and 4 injured after ISIS attacked soldiers, and 4 of the assailants were killed.
A sniper who targeted fleeing civilians killed a 2-year-old boy and injured her mother in the Euphrates River.
4 men were stoned to death near the Tigris river for committing "adultery".

6 men part of a scouting unit for the Libyan army were captured by ISIS. They were executed and pictures of their bodies were posted online. Later on, two suicide bombers killed over 16 more people and injured 7.

Perpetrator: Fulani, ex-Seleka members, and Fulani herdsmen (suspected)
Details: At least 10 people were killed and several injured after armed attackers attacked a region. They now occupy the region.
ISIS crucified 3 people for breaking fast during Ramadan. ISIS has also crucified more people, but the exact number is unknown.
Murder of Jo Cox: Labour Member of Parliament Jo Cox is assassinated by Thomas Mair, a neo-Nazi constituent.
At least 24 people were killed and at least 10 injured after Boko Haram militants attacked a funeral.
An unknown number of people were killed and injured after a suicide bombing attack, another on a series of attacks in the same city.
7 people were killed and 12 injured after an attack on policemen.
One person was killed and 3 injured after a bombing by militants that targeted policemen.
Three people were killed and 10 injured (some serious) after a suicide bombing on the Patriotic Union of Kurdistan headquarters.
4 people were killed and after failing to dismantle an IED inside of a house. The victims were volunteer members of al-Hashd al-Shaabi.
3 escaping civilians were kidnapped and executed by firing squads after attempting to flee ISIS.
3 people were killed after being shot by gunmen inside an agricultural grove. The victims were volunteer members of al-Hashed al-Sha'bi.
7 people were killed after an attack on a Kurdish family. 210 other Kurds were kidnapped by ISIS.
6 members of a family were kidnapped for trying to escape ISIS by firing squad.
1 person was killed and 4 injured after a shelling attack. The person killed was Lieutenant Colonel Hashim Ismail.
A suicide attack was foiled in an orchard by security forces, killing 5 assailants, and leaving an unknown number of other people killed or injured.
3 people were injured and a vehicle damaged after a bombing on army members.
2 ISIS vehicles were destroyed, one containing a suicide bomber who was killed.
2 people were killed and 9 in injured after a bombing near a market.
1 person was killed after an IED bombing near a fertilizer plant.
2 people were injured in a bombing on a road. One person is in critical condition.

Kabul attack on Canadian Embassy Guards: At least 14 or 16 Afghan, Nepali, and Indian security contractors were killed and 9 others were injured when a suicide bomber detonated outside the minibus they were in. The people killed were security guards at the Canadian embassy, and Prime Minister Justin Trudeau condemned the killings.
1 person was killed and 4 injured after an IED bombing. All of the victims were family members trying to escape ISIS.
3 people were killed and 10 injured after a suicide bombing at the al-Taji Camp.
1 person was killed and 8 injured (some serious) after an IED bombing near a market.
An assassination attempt on a politician killed one and injured 5 others, including the politician.
At least 10 people were killed and 40 injured after a bombing in a town square.
At least 2 people were killed after several Boko Haram militants attacked a village, the second attack there by them in a week.
An ISIS sniper killed , Lieutenant Colonel Abbas Abdul-Reda, an important commander in the Iraqi army.
4 people were killed and 5 injured by a suicide bomber who blew himself up while being searcher by policemen.
The media officer of al-Hashd al-Shaabi was injured in a bombing.

6 Jordanian soldiers were killed and 14 Jordanians were injured by a suicide bombing on a border military post in the Rukban Refugee Camp, a makeshift Syrian refugee camp in the extreme northeastern point between Syria and Jordan.
A homeopathic doctor was shot dead by unknown gunmen. The victim was an Ahmadi minority.
During a raid, police killed 3 trainers of suicide bombers who were involved in a terrorist attack in that killed over 20 people.
3 people were executed by ISIS in their self-proclaimed state on an island.
ISIS blew up 5 transmission towers with IEDs.
An IED bombing wounded 4 civilians.
2 people were injured after a shelling attack. Houses were also damaged by the mortars.
1 person was killed and 5 injured after an IED bombing near shops.
1 person was killed and 4 injured after an IED bombing targeting policemen. A vehicle was also damaged.

Amjad Sabri, a popular Pakistani Qawwali Sufi was shot dead by motorcycle-riding Taliban gunmen while driving his car in Karachi. A relative was injured. The attack was condemned nation wide, with Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif also condemning the attack. His funeral was attended by thousands with a Baba Farid descendent leading it.
At least 37 people were killed and 100 injured after a clash between security forces and ISIS. "Dozens" of assailants were killed. 18 more were killed later on.
30 people were killed and dozens more injured after an explosion at an ammunitions depot.
A tribal leader and his son were killed and another person injured after a house was shot at and burned down by ISIS.
2 people were killed and 5 injured after a bombing near a confectionery factory.
A policeman was killed after being shot at by militants.
1 person was killed and 4 injured after an IED bombing targeting al-Hashd al-Shaabi.
1 person was killed and 8 injured after a bombing near a market.
5 civilians were executed by ISIS after being charged for allegedly cooperating with the government.

A Palestinian terrorist driving his car crashed into a couple of Israelis at the entrance to Kiryat Arba. The couple was slightly injured. and soldiers present on the ground have eliminated terrorist.
Five people were killed and fourteen were injured in a car bombing in Benghazi at the Jalaa hospital.
An ISIS sneak-attack was foiled, with 6 of them killed and their vehicle destroyed.

8 people were killed after ISIS attacked a civilians village, burning down 25 houses. At least 27 were injured. Military forces quickly repelled the attack and killed around 135 assailants in the process. At least 12 soldiers were also killed in the process.
June 2016 Mogadishu attacks: Al-Shabaab terrorists detonated a car bomb outside a hotel popular with foreigners and tourists before storming the building and taking hostages.
3 people were killed after an IED bombing that targeted policemen.
A grenade exploded outside a stadium in Antananarivo where people were celebrating Madagascar's independence; one of the wounded later died in the hospital
1 person was killed and 4 injured after an IED bombing that targeted al-Hashd al-Shaabi members.
An ISIS terrorist attacks was foiled and over 25 assailants were killed.

8 people were killed and 20 injured after a shooting attack, where the two attackers were also killed. Some people were critically injured. The attacks come after another attack that injured 4 policemen at a party, and after a top LeT commander was arrested.
At least 4 civilians were killed in another in a series off attacks by Boko Haram militants.
A working policeman was shot dead.
At least 5 people were killed after militants attacked an Ethiopian military base. The death toll of the Al Shabaab militants are currently unknown.
2 people were killed and 1 injured after a bombing on a road.
1 person was killed and 8 injured after a bombing near shops.

Buddhist extremists rampaged a village containing a Rohingya Muslims minority, forcing 70 people to seek shelter and others to flee. Only one man was confirmed injured, yet in the past other raids by Buddhist extremists have killed people, as this attack is another in a series conducted by them.

A series of explosions hit the predominantly Christian town of Qaa where at least four suicide bombers detonated their load, according to a military source. The first attacker blew himself up in front of a house in the village. Alerted, the residents gathered at the site and it is at this time that the three other bombers went into action. More bombers blew themselves up at a funeral that was being organized for those that were killed earlier.

June 2016 Mukalla attacks: At least seven bombings were simultaneously targeted checkpoints in the port city, followed by a fourth that struck the entrance to a military camp. At least 43 people were killed, other sources claiming 50.
2 people were killed after a shooting in an orchard.
1 person was killed and 8 injured after an IED bombing near an industrial area.
2 people were killed and 5 injured after an IED bombing near shops.

2016 Movida Bar grenade attack:8 people were injured after a grenade attack on patrons at the Movida nightclub watching a UEFA European Championships match. The attack was initially thought to be gang-related or due to a business dispute but was later to be found out to be tied to the Islamic State group. The bombing is believed to be the first IS-related attack on Malaysia. According to the Malaysian police, Two people were arrested in July who were ordered by alleged Malaysian IS fighter Muhammad Wanndy Mohamed Jedi. However, Muhammad Wanndy denied that he ordered the attack and said that the two arrested men are Islamic State supporters.
2016 Atatürk Airport attack: Three suicide attackers opened fire on and blew themselves up at Atatürk Airport in Istanbul.
1 person was killed and 5 injured after a bombing in al-Tobji area.
4 people were executed by ISIS after 15 people were kidnapped for allegedly working with the government.
Standardized-Location: Ash Sharqāt, Salah ad Din, Iraq (Sharqat)

Details: A terrorist attack was thwarted and 12 assailants were killed.
4 people were killed after gunmen stormed a civilian house.
An ISIS attack was foiled by a coalition of soldiers and policemen.
14 people were killed and 32 injured after a suicide bombing at a Sunni mosque in Abu Ghraib.
A Hindu Ayurvedic practitioner was hacked to death and beheaded.
1 person was killed and 8 injured after an IED bombing near shops.
2 people were killed and 8 injured after a mortar attack by ISIS targeting escaping civilians.
3 people were killed and 7 injured after a bombing near a market.

At least 10 people were killed and 25 injured after a suicide bomber drove his car into a building and blew himself up. Four more people were killed and 12 injured after a rocket attack onto a neighborhood.
3 people were killed and 6 injured after a terrorist attack on soldiers.
19-year-old Palestinian broke into the bedroom of a 13-year-old girl in a Jewish settlement and stabbed her to death. The attacker was shot dead. Another man was wounded in the fire exchange
A Palestinian from Tulkarm stabbed a man and an elderly woman in Natanya before being shot dead by an armed civilian after a pursuit.

A Coptic priest named Mussa Azmy was shot in the head at a street in Arish and was killed. Islamic State-affiliated Wilayat Sayna claimed responsibility, saying the priest was killed for "warrior against Islam".
Militants detonated a bomb near a hospital in Arish, killing one policemen and wounding another two. Islamic State-affiliated Wilayat Sayna claimed responsibility.

Militants detonated a bomb in a village near Rafah, badly wounding an Egyptian soldier. When escorting the soldier in an ambulance, militants ambushed the ambulance, killing another soldier and wounded the same soldier who was injured in the earlier blast. Islamic State-affiliated Wilayat Sayna claimed responsibility.
6 people were killed and 19 injured after a suicide bombing at a market.
3 people were killed and 9 injured after an IED bombing near a market.
1 person was killed after a gunmen stormed a house and stole Dinars.
1 person was killed and 7 injured after a bombing near shops.

30 June 2016 Afghanistan bombings: At least 40 people were killed and 50 were injured after two Taliban suicide bombers attacked police cadets returning from a graduation ceremony outside of the capital Kabul.
At least 15 people were killed and dozens injured after a suicide bombing that targeted a mosque and a video club.

At least 18 people were killed after a bomb on a roadside went off when a minibus containing a large amount of people passed over it. There were no survivors of the blast in the minibus. The target, a government vehicle, was missed in the bombing, and the blast instead struck the minibus.
A man with extremist views allegedly influenced by ISIS killed his brother, who as the suspect said "did not perform regular prayers and was not religious".
Two adult twin brothers allegedly influenced by ISIS killed their mother and injured two other members of their family for not joining ISIS. The mother's funeral was attended by hundreds.
4 people were killed and 5 injured after an attack on policemen.
3 people were killed and 6 injured after three attacks on policemen, injuring civilians, some seriously.
6 people were killed and 3 injured after a targeted attack on security forces.
Standardized-Location: Qaşr al Farāfirah, New Valley, Egypt (Farafra)

Details: 1 person was killed and 3 injured after a roadside bombing. 2 people were arrested who were suspected of planting the bomb. Bahrain accused Iran's Revolutionary Guards for being behind the bombing, although this is only an accusation, and does not rule out the possibility of terrorism. U.S. Vice President Joe Biden expressed his concerns after the attack. The bombing was described as a "terrorist bombing".

Militants detonated a bomb in a village south of Bahrain's capital Manama, hitting a car carrying four passengers, including a woman who died in the blast and three children who sustained minor injuries. Bahraini authorities said the attack was carried out by "terrorists", but no group claimed responsibility.

Gunmen in a passing vehicle fired at a family vehicle on Route 60 south to Hebron, killing a Jewish yeshiva head from Otniel, causing the vehicle to flip over. His wife was critically injured and his two teenage daughters were lightly injured. The gunmen fled and no group claimed responsibility. On July 27, 2016, the Israeli military conducted a pre-dawn raid which resulted in the death of the suspected perpetrator

Location: Masisi Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: The Nyatura and the Alliance of Patriots for a Free and Sovereign Congo simultaneously attacked several Armed Forces of the Democratic Republic of the Congo positions in the Masisi Territory.

Gunmen fired at two buses within Kenya's Mandera County on the border with Somalia, killing at least six civilians. No group claimed responsibility, but al-Shabaab is suspected. Two people are reported to have been injured.[citation needed]
Six people were killed and nineteen others injured when a suicide bomber blew himself up at a busy market area in western Baghdad.
Six people, including children, were killed aboard a bus during an attack by religious radicals in Kenya.[citation needed]

July 2016 Dhaka attack: A number of gunmen attacked a restaurant popular with foreigners in the wealthy Gulshan Thana area of Dhaka. At least twenty-two civilians, two police officers, and five attackers were killed in shoot-outs and dozens of hostages were taken.
Part of: Internal conflict in Bangladesh, Attacks by Islamic extremists in Bangladesh

Details: Unknown militants detonated a bomb near a shop on the outskirts of Yusufiyeh, south of Iraq's capital Baghdad, killing one man and injuring ten others.

Unknown militants hacked a Buddhist farmer named Mong Shwe Lung Marma (55), a local official of Bangladesh Awami League, to death in southern Bangladesh. Islamic State-affiliated media said the group carried out the attack.
Part of: Internal conflict in Bangladesh, attacks by Islamic extremists in Bangladesh

Details: A Hindu temple worker was hacked to death by three suspected Islamic militants on motorcycles in Jhenaidah. The victim's name was Shaymanonda Das.
Part of: Attacks by Islamic extremists in Bangladesh

Details: Elizabeth Aguilera, a political activist and a local leader of Venezuela's governing socialist political party, was shot dead by a paramilitary group, in retaliation for her work against organized crime in Venezuela. Her body was burned with pictures being posted on-line after her death.
Two gunmen on motorcycles fired at a man on his way to a market in the Dera Murda Jamali area of Balochistan. The gunmen fled the scene and no group claimed responsibility.
Standardized-Location: Dera Murād Jamāli, Balochistān, Pakistan (Dera Murad Jamali)

Details: A Syrian warplane crashed, either from technical problems or being shot down. The pilot, who survived, was then kidnapped and executed.
A suicide bomber on a motorcycle targeted a local tribal elder. The blast killed at least two civilians and wounded eighteen, but the tribal elder was unharmed.
Al-Shabaab militants launched 11 mortars in close succession, killing two girls, aged four and five. 19 civilians were wounded.
An Islamic State sniper assassinated an Iraqi military commander on Khalediya Island, some 20 km east of Ramadi.
An employee of the Iraqi Ministry of Migration and Displacement was shot dead in his vehicle. No group claimed responsibility for the attack
An Islamic State suicide attack was foiled, with an unknown number of attackers killed.
A gunman stormed a house and killed at least seven members of the family. Some family members were able to defend themselves before being killed, and they shot and killed the attacker.
A roadside bomb killed at least four soldiers, with some sources claiming five were killed.

2016 Karrada bombing: At least 346 people were killed, and over 246 injured, in a series of coordinated bomb attacks in Baghdad. Early in the evening of July 3, a large car bomb exploded in the middle of a busy market, killing nearly 346 civilians. The blast occurred in the Baghdad neighborhood of Karrada, which contains Shia Muslims and a large Christian minority. A second car bombing in the district of Sha'ab killed at least 5 people and injured 16, while two more bombings killed at least two more people.
Islamic State executed 15 people. The victims included civilians charged by a court and ex-Islamic State members who were accused of "cowardice".
At least 2 people were killed and 7 injured after an attack by suspected Islamic militants targeting policemen and civilians.
A civilian was killed by gunmen in central al-Maqdadiya.
Seven rebel commanders were killed by a suicide bomber of ISIS.
Near Khartsyzk, a commander of militants was killed in a land mine blast.
A senior Somali military commander, Abdiwali Siad, was wounded in an assassination attempt by unknown gunmen.

Location: Jeddah, Qatif and Medina, Saudi Arabia
Details: 2016 Saudi Arabia bombings: A man blew himself up after police tried to arrest him near the United States consulate in Jeddah. Two Saudi police officers were injured in the blast. Two suicide bombers targeted a Shia mosque in Qatif, but failed to harm anyone but themselves. A suicide bomber targeted security forces outside the Prophet's Mosque in Medina killing 4 and wounding 5 others.
Two people were killed and nine injured after an IED bombing near a market.

At least 50 people were injured when Camp Liberty, a camp housing the People’s Mojahedin Organization of Iran, the main opposition party to the Iranian regime, was shelled. Over 50 rockets and mortar rounds hit the camp, which is located near Baghdad International Airport, causing extensive damage.

Two people were injured when Nigerian troops shot and killed three female suicide bombers who were targeting internally displaced persons in northern Nigeria. The injuries came as a result of one of the suicide bomber's vest exploding.

Location: Beni Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Nine people were killed in a nighttime attack by Ugandan rebels in the city of Oisha, located in the North Kivu province of the DRC.
Standardized-Location: Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: A police officer was injured when a suicide bomber on a motorcycle detonated his explosives after being denied entry to a local police station.
At least 25 people died in a suicide car bombing in the Kurdish-controlled city of Al-Hasakah, Syria.
At least 4 people were killed and 9 injured after two explosions in Baghdad.
Seven Islamic State fighters were boiled to death for attempting to flee the battlefield.
3 people were killed and 12 injured after a shelling attack of three mortars on a refugee camp.
Islamic State militants kidnapped 40 civilians in a town in Aleppo province, and subsequently executed them for trying to escape.
At least nine civilians were injured when a hand grenade was tossed into an open market.
A series of coordinated attacks targeting policemen and mosque attendees left two people dead, and six injured.
Two workers for the telecommunications company Hormud were executed for "cooperating with the enemy", after the government executed several terrorist group members.

RENAMO militants attacked during early morning. According to the commander of the provincial police in Tete Mozambique, Pedro Fabião Nhancololo, the group broke into the residence of the head of the city of Banga and civil registration facilities, and stole all drugs health post.

Militants launched an attack against the airport army headquarters adjacent to Aden International Airport starting with two suicide car bombs. The militants then stormed the facility and engaged in a firefight with security forces. At least 25 security personal were killed and at least 8 were wounded.
Three soldiers of the Israeli army were wounded in an vehicular attack in Gush Etzion. A Palestinian driver rammed a military vehicle at the intersection of Neve Daniel.
A village guard was killed in an attack by outlawed PKK militants in the southeastern province of Hakkâri.
At least 4 people were killed and 2 injured after a suicide bombing that targeted a former Jihadi leader (who was not killed) and his family.
Two civilians were killed and two soldiers injured after attacks by insurgents. The suspected assailants were then attacked in retaliation, with 2 of them being killed.
Gideon Aremun a Nigerian lawmaker and member of the House of Assembly, was assassinated by gunmen.
Militants used homemade explosives and guns to attack policemen guarding an Eid al-Fitr prayer gathering.
At least twelve Libyan soldiers were killed, over 35 injured in the explosion of a car bomb in Benghazi in eastern Libya.
Islamic State executed 5 Sunni tribesmen accused of being with the Popular Mobilization Forces

Muhammad ibn Ali al-Hadi Mausoleum attack: At least 56 people were killed and 75 injured after a suicide car bomb blew up at the gate of the Mausoleum of Sayid Mohammed bin Ali al-Hadi. Gunmen then entered the mausoleum and started shooting at the people inside. Islamic State claimed that they killed over 100 people.
2 Syrian men were making homemade explosives, when they blew up, killing them and injuring a woman who was in another room. Terrorism is suspected.

Perpetrator: al-Nusra Front and others groups suspected
Details: 4 separate rocket attacks ended up with the death of 5 civilians, including children, and the injury of at least 9 people. Many buildings were also damaged.

Two children were killed in a shelling by Islamic State in the Sinai peninsula province militants.The casualties were identified as Reda Ahmed, 16, and his sister Fatma, 6. Their other sibling Mariam, 6, was injured and taken to the Arish general hospital for medical treatment.
The attack on the shrine of seven Dujai: At least 36 people were killed in a bombing near a shrine that is north of Baghdad.
At least 9 people were killed and "dozens" injured after a suicide bombing attack on a Mosque in Borno. There was also a second suicide bombing at another Mosque.
At least 36 people were killed and over 143 injured after mortar and other attacks in Aleppo. Rebel terrorist militant groups were behind the attacks.
Two Russian military personnel were killed when Islamic State shot down their chopper near Palmyra.
10 militants were killed in counter-terrorism raids across the country. 3 members of the Afghan National Security Forces were also killed during the raids
2 soldiers and 1 civilian were killed in a car bombing in Southeast Turkey.
An Israeli driver was moderately wounded in a drive-by shooting.
5 people were executed by Islamic State, including 4 members of a football team, as they consider football "anti-Islamic". 4 other people were also executed for allegedly spying for the Kurdish YPG.

At least 3 people were killed, all children, and 6 injured after an IED blew up when a civilian vehicle drove over it. The Taliban are heavily suspected to be behind the bombing, although they have not claimed responsibility yet. 4 more people were killed and 2 injured after a shooting targeting policemen.
A Christian preacher was hacked to death by suspected Muslim extremists.
Boko Haram militants raided a town with guns and explosives, killing 7 people and damaging buildings.
Two Malian soldiers were killed in an attack near the border with Burkina Faso.
Multiple terrorist attacks by Fulani herdsmen left at least 81 people dead.
The deputy mayor of the Wouro-Mody commune, Kola H. Dia,was killed by terrorists in the Mopti region.
Unknown assailants opened fire on a police vehicle patrolling in the Dereli district. A police officer was injured in the attack.
Another two police officers were wounded when an explosive was detonated near the scene of the first attack .

At least 10 soldiers were killed in a suicide bombing at the Lanta Buro Base near Mogadishu. Militants then entered the base and took control of it. Al-Shabab released a statement claiming that it had killed 30 soldiers.
Two policemen were killed when an IED exploded by their car. Three others were wounded.
At least 12 civilians were killed in a suicide car bombing which targeted a Shiite open market. 5 more people were killed in separate bombings
11 people were killed and 32 injured after a car bomb attack in a market.
Islamic State executed 4 doctors for refusing to fight for them and treat their injured.
A Saudi border guard was killed by a land mine near the border with Yemen.
A Boko Haram attack in Borno State was repelled by the Nigerian Army resulting in the deaths of 25 militants. Two soldiers were killed during the attack.
ISIS executed 7 people from one of their secret prisons in Libya. Three people were found critically injured by Libyan forces, although more may have been likely injured.
Close to President Pierre Nkurunziza, the former minister Hafsa Mossi was murdered in Bujumbura. She had been very quiet since the beginning of the crisis.
At least 7 people were killed in a suicide car bombing which targeted a military checkpoint in northern Baghdad. 11 people were injured, some critically.
2 people were killed and an unknown numbers of attackers were killed after a shooting that targeted a tribal sheikh.

2 people were killed and at least 7 injured after two bombings in and around Baghdad. One bombing was an IED that killed a doctor while he was driving his vehicle, another bombing blew up at a traffic intersection.
Near Krasnohorivka, two Ukrainians soldiers were wounded in a land mine blast.

Location: Rutshuru Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Two people died and two were injured in an attack of AFDRC position in Tongo-Rusheshe in Rutshuru Territory.
Al-Hashd al-Shaabi foiled an attack by Islamic State suicide bombers, killing an unknown number of them. Although, 6 were wounded in other attack on them.
A mass execution by ISIS included 22 police members and 5 members of Peshmerga.
Three marine soldiers were killed by gunmen while they were procuring provisions.
Islamic State shot down a Syrian Arab Air Force fighter jet which likely killed the pilot, crucifying his corpse.

2016 Nice attack: On the evening of 14 July 2016, a 19 tonne cargo truck was deliberately driven into crowds celebrating Bastille Day on the Promenade des Anglais in Nice, France, resulting in the deaths of 86 people and injuring 434.
Eight terrorists opened fire on policemen, injuring 2 of them. The policemen then killed 6 terrorists in retaliation.

Location: Rutshuru Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Two people, aged 25 and 26, were shot dead by Mai-Mai militiamen in Rutshuru Territory in North Kivu. They were killed while chopping wood in the forest.
A roadside bombing killed 2 Kenyan soldiers and one Somali soldier. Militants then engaged in a firefight with the soldiers.
Two civilians, including a child, were wounded early on July 15 when PKK militants staged armed attacks against a military barracks and a police station in the southeastern Siirt Province.
One person was killed and 7 injured after a grenade attack on policemen in Kulgam, India.
An Indian chief was shot dead Saturday in the Venezuelan city of Rosario de Perija in Zulia (west), reported the Public Ministry.
Islamic State burned 5 civilians alive in a cage for allegedly spying and working with the Iraqi security forces.
Three people were killed and 6 injured after an IED bombing near a market.
An IED bombing killed Sami al-Hassan, a leader of Popular Mobilization Forces, while he was in his moving vehicle. It was a targeted attack.
A plot to blow up a bridge over the Tigris River was foiled after an airstrike on a boat carrying many explosives.
Eight militants were killed while seven soldiers were wounded in hostilities this week in the province, sparked by an attack last Wednesday on an Army team studying Moro culture in Mamasapano town.
In Avdiivka, one person was wounded as a result of DPR shelling.
In Marinka, a local woman was wounded as a result of DPR shelling.
1 person was killed and 4 injured after an IED bombing targeting a police patrol, killing one policeman and damaging a vehicle.
5 people were killed and 6 injured after a terrorist group fired 5 rockets into a civilian area, damaging many buildings.

2016 shooting of Almaty police officers: Six people were killed, and eight others were injured following an attack on a police station in Almaty, Kazakhstan’s largest city. One of the attackers has been detained.
An assailant stabbed and injured two soldiers. Responding to the threat, the soldiers shot at the attacker and detained him. He died of his injuries a day later.
Eleven people, including four civilians, were killed and eighteen people were injured in twin suicidal car bombings.
An attack by Islamic State was repelled. The only known casualties are the death of three Islamic State suicide bombers, 3 policemen, and the injury of 5 civilians.
One person was killed and 5 injured after an IED bombing that targeted soldiers. A vehicle was also damaged.

At least 9 soldiers and militants were killed, 25 wounded and four missing after heavy fighting between moderate Islamist militias allied to the former national government and parliament loyal supporters of Tobruk Army, the military said.
An attack by Islamic State on Popular Mobilization Forces injured seven people. Seven Islamic State members were then killed in retaliation.

2016 Würzburg train attack: 5 people were injured, 2 of them critically, when a 17-year-old Afghan asylum seeker attacked passengers on a train with an axe and a knife. The attacker was killed by police.

2016 Nampala attack: Gunmen attacked a Malian Army base near the town of Nampala in central Mali, close to the border with Mauritania. 17 soldiers were killed and 35 others were wounded in the attack, which was jointly claimed by three separate groups.
One person was killed after a Fulani herdsman named Amidu Omuru killed and robbed a man using a shepherd club and a machete.
Seven people were killed and five others wounded during an incursion of armed men in Kibiriz.
In Avdiivka, a 19-year-old man was killed as a result of DPR shelling.
Two suicide bombings killed at least 10 people and injured 18 at Yemeni military checkpoints.
Two bombings in Baghdad resulted in the deaths of a policeman and a member of Popular Mobilization Forces. Three other people were critically injured, and several vehicles were damaged.

Five Malaysian citizens have been kidnapped by the Abu Sayyaf Filipino jihadist group, related to the Islamic State (EI) in waters of the Malaysian state of Sabah in northeast Borneo, the Philippine government said Tuesday.[citation needed]
Suicide bombings by 6 assailants were foiled with an unknown number of assailants killed.
12 protesting civilians were shot dead by Islamic State. In retaliation, Iraqi soldiers killed 20 Islamic State members.
Two people died and five others were wounded after militiamen attacked a truck Kyanyunda.
Al-Shabaab killed at least five soldiers serving with Somali National Army (SNA) in Balad city,30 km southwest of Mogadishu.
A young Palestinian boy named Abdullah Issa was beheaded for allegedly being a member of Liwa al-Quds.
The journalist Pavel Sheremet was killed when a bomb exploded under his car in the center of Kiev.
Islamic State militants executed 33 civilians near Qayyarah.
1 person was killed and 2 injured after a sniper attack at an army checkpoint.
A terrorist attack was foiled by Buraq Popular Mobilization Forces members and border guards with an unknown number of casualties. Vehicles were destroyed.
Five people were killed and 6 injured after a suicide bombing targeting policemen.
Two bombings in and around Baghdad resulted in two deaths and 10 injuries. Several vehicles were also damaged.

Five Mai-Mai militiamen tried to attack a prison in Mitwaba. In the confrontation they beheaded a policeman and cut his body into pieces. The police subsequently killed three militiamen and wounded the remaining two, who were then arrested.
Unknown militants opened fire on a passenger bus, killing at least 2 people.

In the province of Diyarbakır Ergani in the operation organized members of the PKK organization, three policemen were killed and a policeman was injured. Security officers organized operation to an address that was used as a "nest" .One of the two wounded policemen entered the Ergani State Hospital fell despite the effort

2016 Munich shooting: A gunman opened fire on a shopping mall, killing nine before committing suicide. 36 people were wounded, four by gunfire. The shooter was a bullied man who was said to be obsessed with mass shootings. The massacre was conducted on the anniversary of the 2011 Norway attacks. The suspect was described as being a "very nationalistic" racist, with him boasting about similarities with Adolf Hitler.

July 2016 Kabul bombing: Two suicide bombers targeted ethnic Hazaras at a rally in Kabul, killing over 80 people and wounding at least 230 more. Islamic State later claimed responsibility for the attack.
1 person was killed and 4 injured after an IED bombing on an army patrol.
6 people were killed and 8 injured after a roadside bombing targeted civilians attempting to flee Islamic State.
Two IED bombings resulted in the deaths of 3 people and the injury of 13.
An Islamic State suicide bombing attack was foiled by Peshmerga, with at least 5 attackers being killed, 9 being injured, and a vehicle being destroyed.
An Islamic State suicide bombing attack was foiled by the Nineveh Operations with dozens of assailants being killed.

A suicide bombing in the Shiite neighborhood of Kadhimiya in Baghdad left at least 21 people dead. More bombings left 5 people dead and 15 wounded. Islamic State claimed responsibility for the first attack, and is suspected in the others.
An IED bombing killed 1 person and injured 2, targeting families fleeing from Islamic State.
Islamic State burned 3 family members to death, including a 2-year-old-girl, for trying to escape ISIS-held territory.
An Arish police captain was killed in a targeted assassination. Islamic State claimed responsibility.

2016 Ansbach bombing: A 27-year-old Syrian refugee detonated a bomb at a wine bar in Ansbach, killing only himself, but wounding 15 civilians. He had previously been denied entry to a nearby music festival. Authorities found a recorded video message on the attacker's phone, pledging his allegiance the Islamic State.

A Syrian asylum seeker armed with a döner knife attacked a co-worker and bystanders in Reutlingen, Germany, killing the coworker, a pregnant Polish woman, and wounding two other people in the forearm and head, before being subdued by a civilian who hit him with a car and arrested by police.
Three policemen were killed in a PKK roadside bomb attack in Turkey's southeastern Mardin Province.
A suicide car bombing at a checkpoint in central Iraq killed at least 17 people.
An IED bombing at a market in the eastern Baghdad suburb of Al-Amin al-Thaniyah left 2 people dead and 7 injured. Another IED bombing killed 1 and injured 4, and another killed 2 and injured 6.
An Islamic State mortar attack resulted in 30 casualties.
Islamic State executed 23 people for allegedly working with Iraqi forces.

A RENAMO Gunmen from Mozambique’s opposition party Renamo on morning attacked a health centre and a police station in the administrative post of Muapula in the northern province of Niassa. The armed men stole medicines and surgical equipment from the health centre. No casualties have been reported.
Two truck drivers received minor injuries over the weekend when a convoy driving along the EN7 highway was ambushed by gunmen from the opposition party Renamo.

At least thirteen people were killed, and five injured, when two suicide car bombs exploded near an African Union base in the Somali capital of Mogadishu. Al-Shabaab claimed responsibility for the attack.
A truck bomb exploded when passing on a landmine in the eastern city of Van, killing one person and injuring two more.
One soldier was killed and another injured in a rocket attack on a military checkpoint near the Silvan Dam.

2016 Normandy church attack: Two assailants killed a priest and seriously wounded a woman in a church in Saint-Étienne-du-Rouvray. The two assailants were killed by French Special Forces. Islamic State claimed responsibility for the attack.
Multiple bombings in Baghdad left 2 people dead and 9 wounded.
A bombing at the headquarters of Popular Mobilization Forces left an unknown number of casualties.
A family of 5 people was killed in a path-side explosion.
Standardized-Location: Ash Sharqāt, Salah ad Din, Iraq (Sharqat)

Details: 27 July 2016 Qamishli bombings: A terrorist detonated his van packed with explosives at a checkpoint in the Kurdish city of Qamishli. At least 48 were killed and 140 were wounded

A suicide bomber detonated his explosives at a checkpoint in a Shiite neighborhood in Baghdad killing 6 people and wounding at least 15. Other attacks in and around Baghdad killed a further 12 and injured 23 people.
Another series of attacks in Baghdad left at least 12 people dead and at least 24 injured. 4 attackers were also killed in the attacks.
Two separate attacks in Anbar left 3 people dead and at least 4 wounded, including a military commander.
Islamic State executed 25 people in the teacher's institute during their occupation of Fallujah.
A military vehicle exploded when passing on a landmine in the eastern district of Siirt, killing two soldiers and injuring two more.
A bomb detonated in a market selling qat in Marib killing 7 and injuring 18.
Islamic State executed 14 civilians who were attempting to flee the city.

At least 9 people were killed and at least 19 were wounded in several incidents. In the first, an IED bombing in northern Baghdad killed two people and injured eleven others. In the second, an IED bombing in the al-Amel neighborhood in southwest Baghdad killed one person and injured eight others. In the third, a refugee camp in Baghdad was shelled with mortars killing 5 people. Lastly, a suicide bomber killed a police officer named Shafi Alwataifi who prevented him from entering a crowded market by embracing him.
Islamic State executed a person for allegedly working with Iraqi forces.
Two patrons were killed in a shooting in a pub.Four people were injured in the attack.One of the attackers were killed
Mai-Mai attack an army positions in Nyamilima (North Kivu). An old women was wounded.
Islamic State executed 24 civilians in a village near Manbij.
Five soldiers were killed, and 8 were injured in a PKK attack in Çukurca.

A 17-year Mennonite guerrillas kidnapped by Paraguayan People's Army (EPP), read a statement sent today by the armed group that he founded the kidnapping by "the violation of revolutionary laws prohibiting deforestation."
An police patrol was attacked by Islamic State members.

Perpetrator: Front for the Liberation of the Enclave of Cabinda
Details: Front for the Liberation of the Enclave of Cabinda (FLEC) reportedly killed nine Angolan soldiers and wounded 14 others in recent clashes in the oil-rich Cabinda Province. (Reuters)
A bomb killed 2 and injured 8, in a popular market in the south of Baghdad.

A group of 20 armed men invaded the village of the headquarters of the Renamo Mopeia province of Zambezia, in central Mozambique district and occupied the police headquarters for an hour, normalcy returned after the departure of men (RENAMO), after a 45-minute shootout with police.
A roadside bomb exploded by a vehicle carrying paramilitary rangers killing one and wounding eight.

Renamo gunmen overran Sunday Maiaca city in the province of Niassa, northern Mozambique, and attacked the health center, police facilities and the administrator's house, local sources cited by Radio Mozambique.

Two suicide car bombs targeted the Somalia's Criminal Investigative Police Division headquarters killing five civilians and one police officer. Five gunmen then attempted to storm the building but were killed by security forces.

Four gunmen stormed into an oil station of the North Oil Company, situated some 20 kilometers from western Kirkuk. Firing indiscriminately, the gunmen injured two guards and killed four employees who were stationed in the control room. The gunmen then escaped to another oil station 25 kilometers north of the first one where three of then set off their suicide vests. The fourth was killed in a shootout with security forces. One person was killed and 6 were injured at the second oil station.

1. An IED exploded near a lake at Suteih village in Madain district in southern Baghdad, killing two persons and wounding three others. 2. A family of 7 was gunned down by unknown militants who stormed the family's home. 3. An IED bombing in northern Baghdad killed at least 2 and injured 9 others.
A suicide car bomb targeted the headquarters of border police in Anbar Province killing two and injuring five.

Police were able to stop terrorists from killing civilians, and they were attacked instead with an unknown number of casualties. Seven militants were killed. 11 more militants were killed at a different time.[citation needed]

2016 Yerevan hostage crisis: About 20 gunmen took control of a police station, killing two officers. 77 people were injured and 100 others were arrested. 3 gunmen were also injured. Hostages were taken. The gunmen surrendered on July 31, two weeks after seizing the police station.
A captain of the Malian army was shot dead by four AQIM gunmen in Timbuktu in northern Mali.

August 2016 Kabul attack: A massive truck bomb exploded outside a hotel popular with foreigners in Kabul at around 1:30 a.m. local time. The blast was heard throughout the city and much of the city had lost power shortly before the blast. Four gunmen tried to storm the hotel but engaged in a shootout with security forces killing one person and injuring four. Three of the four attackers also died. The Taliban claimed responsibility.
A truck exploded near police cars. Seven policeman were killed and two others injured.

1. A bomb blast at Jafri Naddaf area, south-east of Baghdad killed at least two persons and injured four others. 2. An IED explosion earlier in the day at northeast of Baghdad killed at least one person and injured seven others. 3.
