Ten people have been killed and five injured in a suicide bomb attack near the compound of Afghanistan's intelligence agency in Kabul.
Four policemen were killed during a shooting against Islamic State terrorists in the west of Mosul.
At least four marines were wounded when a explosive charge explode near an army convoy.
Standardized-Location: San José del Guaviare, Guaviare, Colombia

Details: An explosive charge went off while an army patrol was passing in Hawija, leaving two soldiers dead and an officer injured.
One army soldier and an assailant were killed and 14 soldiers were wounded when a suicide car bomb struck an army convoy near a police station in Lashkargah, capital of southern province of Helmand.
2017 Perekrestok supermarket bombing: At least 18 people were injured in a homemade bomb which exploded in a storage locker at a St. Petersburg supermarket.

December 2017 Kabul suicide bombing: A suicide bomber stormed a Shi‘ite cultural center and news agency in the Afghan capital, killing 50 people and wounding scores, many of them students attending a conference. Two other bombs were detonated in the zone.
An explosion apparently targeted a police station in the southern province of Adana. No one was injured in the blast.
A suicide bombing caused by a Boko Haram militant in Borno State killed at least six people and injured 13 others.
Two persons, a police officer and a civilian, were killed during a shooting in a bank. After that, six Egyptian security personnel were killed when a roadside bomb exploded during a terrorist raid.

2017 Saint Menas church attack: Eleven people have died in twin attacks on Coptic Christians in the southern Cairo: eight civilians and a police officer were killed in a shooting outside a church, and two civilians were killed in a Coptic-owned shop beforehand. One attacker was killed by the police.
A tribal figure was killed in an attack by Islamic State against a village in northeastern Diyala.
43 people were injured when two attackers threw a grenade in a night club in northern Colombia.
Boko Haram fighters opened fire on a group of loggers in a remote village in northeast Nigeria, killing 25 people. The gunmen also burned three vehicles laden with firewood heading to Maiduguri.
At least twelve people were wounded in an explosion in Mazar-e-Sharif city, the provincial capital of the northern Balkh province of Afghanistan.
At least two people, including a Somali soldier, were killed after a roadside bomb has ripped through a military convoy in Mogadishu.
Five troopers were killed and three sustained bullet wounds in an attack on a CRPF camp in Jammu and Kashmir’s Pulwama.
An explosion at a funeral in Afghanistan's restive east killed at least 18 mourners and wounded another 13.
At least two people were killed and 30 more were injured in an attack by Boko Haram militants in northern Cameroon.
Five Afghan police officers were killed when a bomb planted by the Taliban blew up in Logar.
Taliban militants allegedly shot dead six members of a family, parents and their four daughters, inside their home in Kohistan district of northern Faryab province.

A police officer was killed while five others were injured when a bomb exploded as the police patrol’s vehicle passed some 400 meters away from the headquarters of the Philippine National Police’s Provincial Police Office in the poblacion.
Two people were killed and 16 others were injured when an improvised bomb went off along a national highway.
23-year old Ahmad Al-H. attacked a man with a knife in a subway-station in Berlin. Before attacking the man, the perpetrator asked the man about his origin and yelled infidel at him.

The Islamic State terrorist group has carried out a huge suicide bombing in eastern Syria against US-backed forces, killing and wounding nearly one hundred pro-Coalition fighters. The attack was delivered by a German jihadist within the faction’s ranks.

Two Russian soldiers were killed in a mortar attack on the Russian Hemeimeem airbase in Syria. More than 10 servicemen were wounded in the attack by “radical Islamists”. At least four Su-24 bombers, two Su-35S fighters and an An-72 transport plane, as well as an ammunition depot, were destroyed by the shelling.
Five civilians and three security officials were injured in two bomb attacks in Chaman.
Two soldiers from the 57th IB were injured when an improvised explosive device went off some 50 meters from the provincial hospital.
A district police chief has been killed in a Taliban attack in the western Farah province. Two other policemen were wounded in the attack in Pusht-e Rod district.
At least three people have been confirmed killed in a blast in Nigeria's northeastern town of Madagali.
Two Egyptian Christians were shot dead by a gunman as they celebrated the New Year at a liquor store.
As many as 12 Frontier Corps soldiers were injured in an explosion in Quetta.

A Central Reserve Police Force jawan was killed after receiving bullet injury in head during exchange of fire between Naxalites at hills of Chakarbandha on the border of Gaya and Aurangabad districts.
Three police officers were wounded when an explosive was detonated in a police car in Kabul.
Five Kenyan policemen were killed in an attack on their vehicle in the county of Mandera, Kenya by Al-Shabaab militants.
Part of: Spillover of the war in Somalia

Details: Three Iraqi lawyers were shot dead by Islamic State militants on a Mosul road.
14 civilians were killed when a suspected Boko Haram militant blew himself up at a mosque in Gamboru, Nigeria. Only the muezzin has survived.
An explosive charge planted by Islamic State militants at Al-Qa’im district in Anbar went off while a police patrol was passing by the area, leaving three security men wounded.
A tribal fighter was killed, while two police personnel were wounded in confrontations with Islamic State members, northwest of Kirkuk.
At least two civilians were killed and four others were wounded in an explosion triggered by a roadside bomb in southern Helmand province of Afghanistan.
Taliban shot dead three Afghan Security personnel in western Farah province.
At least 20 people were killed in a suicide bombing that targeted a mobile police checkpoint in Kabul. As many as 30 others were injured in the incident.
An African Union peacekeeper was killed, and two others were wounded in a landmine explosion in central Somalia.
Assailants shot and killed two civilians at Koodka neighbourhood in Mogadishu.
Two men, including a prominent local traditional elder have been assassinated by gunmen in Afgoye district in Lower Shabelle region.
Rohingya insurgents ambushed a military convoy in Myanmar's Rakhine State, wounding six members of the security forces.
Naxalites gunned down the village sarpanch of Chindugarh village near Koleng in Bastar district of Chhattisgarh.
Four Indian policemen were killed and two others wounded in a bomb attack in the city of Sopore.

Perpetrator: Movement of Democratic Forces of Casamance (suspected)
Details: At least 14 people were killed and seven injured when gunmen open fire in the region of Casamance, in southern Senegal.

An explosive charge went off near an overcrowded market at al-Yusufiyah area in southern the Iraqi capital, leaving three people injured. Later, another explosive device was detonated near a café in the neighborhood of al-Saheroon in southeast Baghdad, killing one person and injuring four others.
A policeman was killed while another was injured in a landmine explosion at Al-Qa’im district in Anbar.
At least 34 people were killed and 70 others injured in four explosions in Syria's northwestern city of Idlib.
At least three people were killed and eight others wounded when insurgents stormed a security checkpoint in Afghanistan's eastern Kunar province.
At least nine Afghan army soldiers were killed and 20 others wounded after Taliban militants attacked an army camp in Uruzgan province, south of Afghanistan.
At least one civilian was killed in an attack by members of the terror group Boko Haram in Cameroon's Far North region.
At least two Somali soldiers were injured in a grenade attack on an army checkpoint outside Beledweyne, the regional capital of Hiran.

Gunmen on motorbikes opened fire on a group of loggers collecting firewood at Kaje village, near the Borno state capital, Maiduguri. 20 People were killed in the attack and 15 others are missing and presumed kidnapped by the attackers.
A bomb explosion in the heart of Mogadishu, the Somali capital has wounded at least three government soldiers aboard a military vehicle.
A bomb went off in the center of the Pakistani city of Quetta, capital of the province of Balochistan, killing seven people and wounding 23.
A drive-by shooting took place in the Northern West Bank leaving one Israeli, a rabbi, dead.
A soldier was killed while two civilians were injured when a suspected Islamic State-inspired Moro armed group set off two separate roadside bombs in Maguindanao.
One civilian was injured in a bomb blast in southeastern Miqdadiyah, Diyala.
Six members of a ranger patrol were hurt when a roadside bomb exploded as they went by in Nong Chik district.
At least three Yemenis were killed in a suicide car bomb attack that targeted a military vehicle in Yemen’s southeastern Shabwah province. Three Yemeni soldiers were also injured in the incident.
At least three people were killed in an attack in Cameroon's Far North region.
Five personnel of Afghan Local Police were killed and two others wounded following an attack from the Taliban militants in the country's troubled northern province of Kunduz.
A Colombian soldier was shot dead by a ELN sniper in the department of Arauca.
Three French soldiers of the Barkhane force were wounded, one of them seriously, by a suicide bomber in eastern Mali.
Six policemen have been killed in a Taliban attack in Nawa district of southern Helmand province.

A German prisoner jailed for his involvement in the Djerba bombing in 2002 assaulted four guards at the Vendin-le-Vieil prison while shouting "Allahu Akbar". One of the guards was hospitalized for a head wound.
At least one civilian was killed and several were wounded after mortar rounds landed near the Presidential Palace in Mogadishu.
Two suicide bombers, alleged members of the Islamist group Boko Haram, detonated their bombs in the Ouro-Kessoum district of Amchide in Cameroon, injuring two others.
Four people were killed and two others kidnapped in separate overnight attacks in the far north of Cameroon. Another one was wounded.
A Taliban attack has killed three policemen in western Farah province.
Islamic State militants killed three family members in their house in the oil-rich province of Kirkuk.
Two people were killed and six others injured in a suicide blast in Chaghcharan, the capital of western Ghor province.
A menonite farmer (called Abraham Fehr) was found dead in San Pedro Departament, Northern of Paraguay.
A suicide bombing in Baghdad has killed eight and wounded up to 24 others.

One person was killed and five police injured when Al-Shabaab militants attacked a convoy of buses at Nongoro area along the Lamu-Malindi highway. Two Toyota land cruisers used by the police were destroyed during the incident.
Part of: Spillover of the war in Somalia

Details: Islamists attacked a community from the administrative post of Olumbe, Palma district and killed seven people and burned down houses.
Gunmen have shot dead a Christian man in the turbulent north of the Sinai Peninsula
Militants of the ELN kidnapped a contractor of Ecopetrolun in the Departament of Arauca.
At least five Somali soldiers were wounded when their military vehicle hit a landmine in Mogadishu.
Al-Shabaab fighters attacked a remote Somali army base north of the capital Mogadishu, killing at least two Somali government soldiers.
A Turkish soldier was killed and three others wounded after an explosion of a guided missile shot by PKK militants at a Turkish military base in Hakkari province.
Four Turkish soldiers were killed in bomb explosions in Al Zab.
A Coptic Christian man has been shot dead by gunmen in Egypt's Sinai Peninsula.

Six Afghan National Army soldiers were killed and two others surrendered to the Taliban in the Qaisar district of northwestern Faryab province. Separately, four policemen have been injured in a Taliban attack on a police check-post in the Chalgazai area of Qaisar.
At least seven police force members were killed in a Taliban ambush in Farah province. Another three police force members were wounded.
2018 Baghdad bombings: 38 people were killed and at least 105 others wounded in two suicide bombings at Baghdad’s al-Tayaran Square.
Four people were killed in Mayo-Tsanaga, a region of the Far North of Cameroon, during an attack by Boko Haram. The assailants left after burning down dozens of huts and a church.

Location: North Kivu, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Three Democratic Republic of Congo soldiers were killed while repelling an attack in the eastern Beni region by ADF Ugandan extremist rebels. Five others were wounded.
Standardized-Location: Butembo, Nord Kivu, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: At least five security personnel lost their lives and six others were injured when a vehicle carrying them turned over after being ambushed in Balochistan's Kech district.
Six people were killed by gunmen who also abducted five girls who joined the loggers to collect firewood from the Jinene woods.
Five people, including two suspected fighters of the terror group Boko Haram, were killed in an attack near Nigeria's northeastern town of Madagali. Two others were critically injured.
A police constable was gunned down by gunmen on Quetta's Raisani Road.
A drive-by shooting outside an office in North Mitrovica killed the head politician of the Kosovo Serb party called Freedom, Democracy, Justice, Oliver Ivanović.

At least five people were killed in a mortar attack on a market in northern Afghanistan. 45 people, including women and children, were also wounded in the attack in Khwaja Sabz Push district of Faryab Province.
Taliban militants have beheaded an Afghan Local Police member in the Mohammad Agha district of central Logar province.
Standardized-Location: Muḩammad Āghah Wuluswālī, Logar, Afghanistan (Mohammad Agha)

Details: A senior officer known for leading raids on militant hideouts escaped assassination when a suicide bomber riding on a motorcycle blew himself up near his vehicle in the port city of Karachi. The bomber had an unknown number of accomplices who opened fire at the car after the explosion. Guards returned fire, killing two of the gunmen.
At least two civilians were killed and a dozen others injured in a suicide attack near a mosque in the Far North Region.
A policeman was injured in a sniper attack by the militant Islamic State group in Baqubah, the capital of Diyala province.
Two Iraqi police officers were killed and seven others injured in a bomb blast in Diyala province.
Two suspected Boko Haram suicide bombers killed 12 people and injured 65 others in an attack in the northeastern Nigerian city of Maiduguri.
Suspected Boko Haram fighters killed at least seven soldiers in an attack on a military post in Niger's southeastern Diffa region. Ten others were injured in the attack.
A police captain was killed and four conscripts were injured after terrorists detonated an explosive device on the International Coastal Road.

Israeli special forces shot and killed an armed Palestinian man suspected to have been behind a drive-by shooting terror attack that killed Rabbi Raziel Shevach near a West Bank settlement outpost. Two Israeli special forces members were wounded during the raid.
Eight police and Afghan National Army soldiers have been killed in attacks on security posts in the capital and Anar Dara district of western Farah province.
Gunmen shot dead a mother and her daughter who were part of a polio vaccination team in Quetta.
At least eight policemen were killed and two others wounded when Taliban attacked a security check post in Helmand province.
Boko Haram jihadists have killed five people in an attack on a village in Adamawa state, northeast Nigeria.

Two explosions rocked Barangay Semba, likely the handwork of the Bangsamoro Islamic Freedom Fighters. No one was hurt in the twin blasts but shrapnel hit the gate of a nearby house and several trees in the area.

Uniformed soldiers who were in an army base in the municipality of Teorama, Norte de Santander, were attacked in an unexpected attack by members of the ELN guerrillas. One soldier was killed and two more were injured.
Eight policemen were injured after terrorists hurled a grenade at a Tehsil office in south Kashmir’s Pulwama town.
A Palestinian driver rammed IDF soldiers at a checkpoint near Qasr el Yahud in the West Bank, lightly injuring three men.

Location: North Kivu, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: 22 soldiers were killed in Democratic Republic of Congo’s volatile eastern borderlands where the army is battling Ugandan Islamist rebels. More than 20 other Congolese soldiers were also wounded after gunmen launched an attack during the night near the town of Eringeti in North Kivu province.
Standardized-Location: Butembo, Nord Kivu, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: Terrorists hurled a grenade at a police station in Jammu and Kashmir’s Shopian district. No person was injured in the explosion.
A policeman was injured after Naxalites triggered an improvised explosive device near a market in Chhattisgarh’s insurgency-hit Dantewada district.
Seventeen members of the public uprising forces and a local police commander were killed in an attack by the Taliban in Balkh province.

2018 Inter-Continental Hotel Kabul attack: Gunmen launched an attack on the Inter-Continental Hotel Kabul, according officials from Afghanistan's Ministry of Interior Affairs. More than 100 people have been freed from the hotel and six gunmen have been killed. 40 people are confirmed dead and at least 22 have been injured. Taliban claimed responsibility, and the Afghan officials said that Haqqani Network militants carried out the attack.
A roadside bomb has killed at least 12 civilians in the western Herat province. A 13th person was wounded in the explosion, which struck a vehicle in the Gulran district.
Four Afghan National Army soldiers have been killed and three others injured in a Taliban attack in the Nahri Saraj district of Helmand province.
Seven policemen were killed and an eighth wounded after Taliban militants stormed their check posts in the Garmsir district of southern Helmand province.
Armed assailants shot dead a former police officer, who was fired over the 2011 killing of five Chechen women, in a hit-and-run attack in Quetta.

Location: North Kivu, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Suspected Ugandan Islamist rebels killed three civilians in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo.
Standardized-Location: Butembo, Nord Kivu, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: A caravan made up of members of the National Protection Unit, along with members of the FARC political party, who were returning from a meeting in the village of El Oasis, was attacked by gunfire in the department of Arauca. One of the vehicles that was part of the caravan was incinerated and a civilian who was part of an oil company in the sector was killed in the attack.
A motorcycle bomb killed three civilians and wounded two dozen others at a bustling morning market in Yala in Thailand's insurgency-hit south.

A bomb planted by Islamic State inside a house in central Rawa district in Anbar exploded once a six-strong family entered it following a long period of displacement, leaving two of the family members dead and four others injured.
A civilian was injured in a grenade attack by terrorists who were targetting the security forces in Pampore in Jammu and Kashmir.
A policeman was injured after terrorists lobbed a grenade near Baramulla Police station in Jammu and Kashmir.
Four people have been killed and six others wounded in a remote-controlled improvised explosive device explosion near Mogadishu.

A twin car bombing outside a mosque in Benghazi left at least 41 people dead and 80 injured. No group has claimed responsibility for the bombing, but many assumed it was the work of remnants of an Islamic State in Iraq and Syria group faction largely driven out of Libya.

2018 Save The Children Jalalabad attack: A complex attack began with a suicide car bomb outside the Save The Children offices in the city of Jalalabad, followed by gunmen entering the compound and fighting Afghan special forces. At least six people were killed and 27 others were wounded in the attack.
Four police personnel, including two sub-inspectors, were killed and seven others injured in a gun-fight with Naxals in Chhattisgarh's Narayanpur district.
Two Malian customs officers have been killed in a suspected jihadist attack at a market in the small village of Toubakoro.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: Two militants and a teenage boy were killed and two girls critically injured during a gunfight between militants and government forces in Chaigund village of south Kashmir’s Shopian.
A car bomb went off near a Shia mosque in a southern suburb of Kirkuk, causing damage to the holy site. No casualties were reported.
A landmine explosion blew up a civilian passenger vehicle in central Mali, killing 26 people and wounding several others.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: In Youwarou, in Central Mali's Mopti region, Malian armed forces killed seven terrorists. Two Malian soldiers were also killed in the operation.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: Two civilians were killed while another was injured in an improvised bomb explosion in the middle of a ricefield in Datu Piang town in Maguindanao.
Communist insurgents killed an Army officer and wounded 2 soldiers in a firefight in Davao City, in southern Philippines.
Six children and an adult civilian were killed when a rocket hit their home in Ghazni Province. Three other people were injured in the attack.
At least four people were killed and thirteen others injured when a suicide car bomb exploded in Kandahar.
Terrorists hurled a grenade at a police station in Jammu and Kashmir's Pulwama district. No casualty or injury has been reported.
At least three people were killed when Boko Haram attacked the Hyambula village in northeast Adamawa state. Five others were injured in the attack.
At least six security force members were wounded when a suicide bomber in a Toyota Corolla detonated his explosives in the Nad Ali district of Helmand Province.

2018 Kabul ambulance bombing: At least 103 people were killed and 235 others injured when a Taliban suicide bomber exploded an ambulance laden with explosives near Sidarat Square in central Kabul where several government offices are located.
14 people were killed and 22 wounded in an attack on a camp in Soumpi, in Mali's restive north. Two terrorists have also been killed.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: 28 people were injured in an attack on a police station in San Lorenzo, in Northern Ecuador.
Standardized-Location: San Lorenzo de Esmeraldas, Esmeraldas, Ecuador

Details: At least five police officers were killed and 42 others injured in a bombing attack that targeted a police station in the northern coastal city of Barranquilla.
In the town of Buenavista, Santa Rosa del Sur, an explosive device was hurled against the police substation in that area. The incident left two police officers dead and one injured.
Standardized-Location: Santa Rosa del Sur, Bolívar, Colombia

Details: Two KDF soldiers were killed after their truck run over an Improvised Explosive Device at Handaro, Holugho sub-county, Garissa county. Three other soldiers, who tried to jump off the vehicle, were reportedly shot at close range by the suspected militias and were seriously wounded.
Part of: Spillover of the war in Somalia

Details: An IDF soldier sustained minor injuries in a car ramming attack near Herzliya.
Al-Shabaab militants have shot and killed an assistant judge in Wanlaweyn district in Somalia's Southern Lower Shabelle region.
Five Malian soldiers were killed and several others injured in an attack on a military base in Ménaka, in northeastern Mali.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: At least five people were injured in an attack against the police in the metropolitan area of the Colombian city of Barranquilla.

Eleven Afghan soldiers were killed and sixteen others were injured when five Islamic State militants attacked an army post in Kabul. Four attackers were later killed by the security forces, and another was arrested.
Gunmen have killed two policemen who were patrolling a market in Burkina Faso's northern Baraboulé district.
Two IS extremists attacked a Hashd al-Shaabi checkpoint in the Hawija district, southern Kirkuk Province, killing one fighter and wounding three others.
One member of the Iraqi Federal Police was killed, and another one was wounded during a raid on a house in a village near the al-Multaqa sub-district, southwest of Kirkuk.
At least two soldiers were killed overnight while fighting off an attack by suspected Boko Haram jihadists in southeast Niger.
A Somali army colonel and three soldiers were killed following an attack on a convoy by Al-Shabaab militants in Bay region in Southern Somalia.
At least eight people of a family were killed and another one injured as a result of a bomb explosion in the Maqbal area of Upper Kurram Agency.
Boko Haram jihadists killed at least five loggers in northeast Nigeria. Four others were injured in the attack.
About 22 newly-recruited Yemeni soldiers were killed when a suicide car bombing struck a military checkpoint in the southeastern province of Shabwah. Several others were wounded in the attack.
An explosive charge planted by Islamic State militants inside a house in the Old City of Mosul went off, injuring a man and his wife.
A roadside bomb hit a military vehicle carrying Puntland soldiers in the vicinity of Galgala hills of Bari region, killing at least one soldier, wounding 3 others.

A civilian support worker for the Turkish Armed Forces was killed in a terrorist car bomb attack on a military convoy in Syria’s northwestern Idlib province. One Turkish soldier and another civilian employee were also injured in the explosion.
Two Malian soldiers were killed and seven wounded when their vehicle hit an improvised explosive device near Gao in northern Mali.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: Islamic State members have assassinated a former general of the Iraqi military in the southwest of Kirkuk. In another incident, two police officers were killed and another two injured while attempting to defuse an explosive device.
A civilian has been killed and three others have been injured when their vehicle struck a roadside bomb in the Al-Taji district of Baghdad province.
Four people were killed and 44 others sustained injuries in multiple suicide bomb attacks at a Konduga community and the Dalori Internally Displaced Persons camp.

Three Turkish soldiers were killed and seven wounded in cross-border attacks carried out by the outlawed Kurdistan Workers’ Party (PKK) from northern Iraq, targeting the eastern Turkish province of Hakkâri .

A bomb from the remnants of the Islamic State exploded targeting a border guards patrol near al-Waleed border crossing, west of Anbar. The blast left one of the personnel killed and four others wounded, in addition to damages caused to the patrol.
Terrorists attacked a post manned by a joint team of Jammu and Kashmir Police and CRPF at Banura area of south Kashmir’s Pulwama district. No casualties have been reported.
A roadside bomb explosion killed at least three people and wounded two others in an area outside Mogadishu, the Somali capital.
Three people were slightly injured in an explosion in the building of the Tax Directorate in Ankara.
Two people were killed while four others were wounded when Abu Sayyaf bandits waylaid a private vehicle in Patikul, Sulu.
A suicide bomber blew himself up when FC personnel foiled his entrance in Sheikhwasil Check Post after hectic efforts and firing. Two security personnel were partially injured in the suicide blast.

Two women and a child were killed after the vehicle they were travelling in struck a roadside bomb in the Gelan district of southeastern Ghazni province. Another three children, one woman and one man were wounded in the blast that took place in Chirlai area of the district.
Five guards of a political party have been killed and four others wounded in a Taliban attack in Shirin Tagab district of northwestern Faryab province.

Location: Beni Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Three people were killed in an attack by Ugandan Muslim rebels of the ADF who also looted a hospital in the eastern Democratic Republic of Congo.
Standardized-Location: Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: Five persons, including three CRPF personnel, were injured in a grenade attack in Batagund area of Tral in south Kashmir’s Pulwama district.
At least two civilians were killed in an attack by the terror group Boko Haram in Kolofata of Cameroon's Far North region.
FARC dissidents blew up an energy tower in the southeastern Colombian department of Guaviare, which left some 22,000 people in the area without electricity.
Standardized-Location: San José del Guaviare, Guaviare, Colombia

Details: At least 11 security officials were killed and 13 injured in a suicide attack near a military camp in Swat district of Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa.
One policeman has been killed and six others wounded in an attack in the Bala Buluk district of western Farah province.
At least four civilians were killed by suspected Islamists in the Gao region of northern Mali. The assailants also took hostages during the attack, at least one of which was killed later.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: A roadside bomb targeted a pickup truck carrying members of the security forces in the turbulent north of the Sinai Peninsula, killing three. Five other members of the security forces and a civilian were wounded in the attack.
Boko Haram fighters stormed a village in northeast Nigeria and killed three people. Seven others were injured in the attack.

One person has been reported dead after Boko Haram terrorists attacked Kala village, opposite the Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) camp in Dalori, Borno State. The attackers also injured another man during the attack and burnt down some houses.
Six people were killed and two others injured in the Cameroonian town of Hitawa (Far North), following an attack by Boko Haram.
Terrorists attacked a police station at Hombori. No one was killed or hurt in the attack.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: Suspected jihadists killed two Malian soldiers overnight in the country's unstable north.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: At least 4 people have been killed and 5 others injured in a bomb explosion inside a house in the Somali capital Mogadishu.
Armed men threw a grenade at a house in Ituango and fired repeatedly at its facade. The incident left a 3-year-old girl dead.

One Lebanese army soldier was killed and 7, including two officers, were injured during a raid the army launched to arrest suspects in the northern port city of Tripoli. A suspect was shot and killed while another one was arrested.
Part of: Spillover of the Syrian Civil War

Details: 2018 Ariel stabbing: An Israeli man was stabbed to death in a terror attack at a bus station outside the West Bank settlement of Ariel.
Terrorists attacked the Rashtriya Rifles camp in Kakapora with a grenade. No loss of life or any injury has been reported in the incident.
Six paramilitary Hashd al-Shaabi fighters were killed in an attack by Islamic State militants in Iraq's eastern province of Diyala.
Gunmen have opened fire on two Chinese nationals in Pakistan's southern port city of Karachi, killing one and wounding the other.
A man was killed and eight other people were injured in a bomb blast targeting a pro-government in Panjgur.
Guerrillas of the National Liberation Army (ELN) destroyed a stretch of the Caño Limón-Coveñas pipeline in northeastern Colombia with explosives.
One Afghan Local Police member was killed and seven others were wounded in a Taliban attack on a check-post in southern Helmand province.
Assailants have shot and killed a former district commissioner in Beledweyne, the regional capital of Hiran province in central Somalia.
A Turkish soldier was killed and six people wounded in a rocket and mortar attack on the Turkish military in Syria's northwestern province of Idlib.
Two policemen were killed after militants attacked a government-run hospital in Srinagar that allowed a hardened Pakistani terrorist to escape.
An explosive charge planted by terrorists went off at al-Mada’in district, southeast of Baghdad, leaving two civilians wounded.
A defence volunteer, a school-mum and a young student were wounded when a bomb exploded near a school in Yala’s Yaha district.
Three civilians were killed and 15 others injured in a mortar attack carried out by PKK-affiliated People's Protection Units (YPG) in northwestern Syria's Afrin region.
At least six civilians were killed and 30 injured in Damascus and its surroundings by attacks of terrorist groups using mortars.
At least five soldiers were wounded in an overnight attack on a Police Station in Bosaso, the main commercial city of Somalia's northeastern semi-autonomous region of Puntland.
At least two people were killed in an attack on a police station by Al-Shabaab militants in Jalalaqsi town in Hiran region of central Somalia.
At least three people were killed in separate shootings in Mogadishu by Al-Shabaab assassins.

Four policemen, who were commanders of their posts, were killed after they were ambushed by Taliban militants in Chora district. Another four policemen were wounded in the attack in Akhtar village of the district.
The Taliban shot dead three members of a family in Urozgan province.
At least two security personnel were killed and four others injured when their vehicle came under attack in Pakistan's northwest tribal area of North Waziristan.

Seven people were wounded in two bomb explosions in the north and southeast of Baghdad. Earlier, a female suicide bomber was killed as she was trapped by Iraqi troops inside a Baghdad school before blowing herself up.
A security guard was lightly wounded in a stabbing attack in the settlement of Karmei Tzur in Gush Etzion. Another security guard opened fire and killed the terrorist.
A tribal elder was killed in a remote-controlled explosion in Bajaur Agency. Several others were injured in the attack.
A senior Somali military officer was assassinated in Mogadishu, the Somali capital.
Five Somali soldiers were killed and four others wounded in a roadside explosion in Afgooye district in Lower Shabelle region.
At least one person was killed and fourteen others were wounded in a suicide bombing in Ramadi city, west of Anbar.
A civilian was killed and two others were injured in a bomb blast in Taji district, north of Baghdad.
Seven people have been killed and three injured in a shooting in Khanaqin.
Twin bomb blasts struck a mosque in Benghazi in eastern Libya, killing at least two people and wounding 143.
One soldier has died as a result of rocket fire by PKK terrorists in Çukurca, Hakkâri province in south-eastern Turkey.
Momena Shoma, a Bangladeshi national, stabbed a 56-year-old man in the neck while he was asleep at his Callistemon Rise home in Mill Park.
Five civilians were killed and another 18 wounded in central Mali when their passenger vehicle struck a landmine.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: At least four local cricket players were killed and two civilians wounded in an explosion in Bati Kot district of Nangarhar province.
Six security personnel have been killed and eight others wounded in a Taliban attack on a check-post in the Nawa-I-Barakzayi district of southern Helmand province.

Location: Beni Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Five people were killed in an ADF attack on the locality of Ngite. One person was injured, houses burned down, shops looted and several people were still unaccounted for.
Standardized-Location: Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: The National Liberation Army (ELN) activated explosive charges that damaged a bridge and road in the department of Cesar (north), leaving no victims.
Terrorists have shot and killed a Shia Muslim in Dera Ismail Khan district of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa.
Standardized-Location: Dera Ismāīl Khān, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Pakistan (Dera Ismail Khan)

Details: Two footballers have been killed and three others wounded in a roadside blast in Anar Dara district of western Farah province.
A Taliban infiltrator killed 16 members of a pro-government militia force in the insurgency ridden southern province of Helmand when he turned his gun on men who he had worked with for months.
A car bomb struck a checkpoint 90 kilometers east of the coastal Libyan city of Sirte, injuring at least four troops.
A car bombing killed at least seven civilians and injured 30 others in Syria’s northwestern Idlib.
Al-Shabaab militants attacked Afgooye town, about 30 km southwest of Mogadishu. Three civilians were injured in the attack.
2018 Sunjuwan attack: Jaish-e-Mohammed terrorists attacked an Army camp in Jammu, killing five soldiers and a civilian and injuring ten others. Three terrorists were also shot dead by the Army.
A District Reserve Guard was killed when a pressure bomb planted by Naxalites went off in Chhattisgarh's Bijapur district.
Terrorists fired five to seven rounds at an Army camp in Chilli Pora in Kashmir's Shopian. No casualties were reported.
A knife-wielding attacker wounded four church-goers in the Indonesian city of Yogyakarta, before being shot by police.
Six bomb blasts in the Pattani province left nine people, including the Yaring district chief, injured.
Taliban militants have kidnapped 10 tribal elders in the Dayan district of northwestern Jowzjan province.
An explosion caused by the remnants of the Islamic State in al-Qa'im town, on the borders with Syria, left a civilian killed and two others seriously wounded.

Saad Ismael, a member of al-Abbara town council and his uncle Sheikh Mahmoud al-Baiyati, a tribal leader, were wounded when three roadside bombs detonated outside Islamil's house in the town of al-Abbara in Diyala province.
A car bomb attack in the Maarrat Misrin area of Idlib killed 9 people and injured 14 others.
Colombian soldier Jhon Jairo Delgado Bastidas was killed by guerrillas of the National Liberation Army (ELN) in the municipality of Valdivia, in the department of Antioquia.
The railway line of Colombia's largest coal mine, Cerrejón, was attacked with explosives that caused the suspension of trains without affecting production or exports.
A 45-year-old man, an activist of Hurriyat Conference, was killed after fired upon by suspected terrorists in Charangam area of Beerwah in Central Kashmir’s Budgam district.
Two Kenyans have been stabbed to death by Al-Shabaab fighters for allegedly spying for Somalia and Kenyan intelligence services in Qunyo Barrow town, Lower Shabelle region.

Two holed up terrorists were killed in a gunfight with security forces at Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF) camp in Srinagar's Karan Nagar. A CRPF trooper was killed during the gunfight while a constable of the Special Operations Group (SOG) of the Jammu and Kashmir Police was injured.
Suspected militants opened fire at Domana army camp in Jammu. No one was killed or injured in the attack.
A dead policeman, identified as mayor Jorge Sáenz Animero, and three civilians injured, is the result of an attack perpetrated by armed men in the capital of Arauca.
Five soldiers, including a captain, were killed and two others wounded in an explosion of an improvised explosive device in Tebessa province near the Algerian-Tunisian border.
Tehrik-i-Taliban Pakistan militants shot dead four paramilitary soldiers in Quetta.
A Taliban attack killed seven policemen in western Farah province. The hours-long fighting also killed three insurgents.
In northern Faryab province, a Taliban attack killed three policemen in Qaysar district. Ten Taliban insurgents were also killed in the attack.
Members of the Abu Sayyaf Group abducted a government engineer in Jolo, Sulu.
Two children were killed in a landmine explosion in western Herat province.
Three female students and three local security volunteers were injured when a bomb exploded near a primary school in the Mueang Yala district in Yala province.
One person has been injured after an explosive device attached to his vehicle went off in Waberi district.
A bomb exploded in the Paloquemao sector of Bogotá. The attack did not leave people injured.
Terrorists shot indiscriminately and lobbed a grenade before escaping from a security forces cordon in Palhallan area of Baramulla district.

Four people, including three teachers, were killed while another was injured when Al-Shabaab militants attacked Qarsa Primary School in Wajir County. One security vehicle responding to the attack ran over an explosive, but no officer was injured.
Part of: Spillover of the war in Somalia

Details: A leading tribal elder and chief of a local peace committee was killed in a bomb blast in Bajaur Agency.
At least two Puntland soldiers were killed in a roadside bomb blast in Galgala Mountains of Bari region. Another was injured in the attack.
At least three Yemeni soldiers were killed and several wounded in a roadside bomb explosion in the country's southern province of Abyan.
At least 21 persons were killed and 70 civilians injured as three bombers struck Konduga local government area of Borno State.
Taliban militants attacked a police checkpoint in Bala Buluk district in Farah, killing at least 10 officers.
At least five police officers were killed and two others injured in a Taliban attack in Mullah Din area of Qalat city.
An explosive device wounded four Israeli soldiers, two severely, near the border fence with the Gaza Strip.
Two soldiers were killed and another wounded in a terrorist attack in the municipality of Djellal, Algeria.

Location: Beni Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Five people were killed and eight others injured in an ambush by Ugandan Islamist rebels in the Beni territory of Democratic Republic of Congo’s east.
Standardized-Location: Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: An explosive device planted by terrorists near shops in the region of Radwaniyah, southwest of Baghdad, exploded, causing the injury of a civilian.
Two soldiers were killed and five others injured in an attack in Iraq's western Anbar province.
Islamic State militants ambushed a convoy of pro-government militia fighters in the Hawija district of Kirkuk province, killing at least 27 of them.

Kizlyar church shooting: Five people were killed and five others were injured in a shooting carried out by an Islamic State militant at a Christian church in Kizlyar, Russia. The attacker was shot and killed by police officers.
A car bomb exploded in the Kurdish-dominated city of Qamishli in northeastern Syria, killing five people and injuring seven.

Two personnel of the Chhattisgarh police and a civilian were killed and six others injured in a gunfight with the outlawed CPI (Maoist) at Bhejji in Sukma district, south Chhattisgarh. The security forces killed one Maoist in another exchange of fire at Errabore.
Four persons, including the NCP candidate Jonathone Nengminza Sangma, were killed and three others injured in an improvised explosive device blast in Meghalaya's East Garo Hills district, India.
Five soldiers, including a junior officer, were injured in a roadside bombing in Datu Unsay, Maguidanao.
Six members of the elite Special Action Force were wounded in an attack staged by New People’s Army rebels in Barangay San Jose in Antipolo City.
Three civilians, including a woman, were killed in a roadside bombing in Shib Koh district of western Farah province.
In Ghazni province, Taliban insurgents stormed an Afghan Local Police check-post in Laghaba locality of Dih Yak district, killing one policeman and injuring three others.
In Paktika province, a policeman was killed after Taliban gunmen attacked a check-post in Sharana, the provincial capital.
Five police officers were killed and six others injured when armed Taliban militants attacked a checkpoint in Nad Ali district of Helmand province.
At least 24 policemen were killed in western Farah province during coordinated attacks by the Taliban.
Two soldiers were injured in an attack by dissidents of the former Colombian FARC guerrilla against Ecuadorian soldiers on the border with Colombia.

Dapchi schoolgirls kidnapping: 111 students from one school and two other students from another school were abducted by Boko Haram in Dapchi, Nigeria. The insurgents later released 107 of them, 5 are reportedly dead and one is still in custody.
Three tribal leaders were killed and two others wounded in a bombing that targeted a hotel room in the city of Jalalabad in the Nangarhar province in eastern Afghanistan.
At least six people were killed and five others injured in a Boko Haram attack in the department of Mayo Tsanaga in Cameroon's Far North region.
Terrorists opened fire and lobbed grenades at the Indian Air Force facility in Awantipora area of south Kashmir’s Pulwama district. No loss of life or property has been reported.
Terrorists attacked a police check post with hand grenades in Peshawar. No one was hurt in the attack.
Five national intelligence agency personnel have been killed following an armed attack in Bagram district of Parwan province.
An attack by the Taliban on a check-post in Zabul province killed an Afghan policeman and injured two others.

At least seven peasants were injured as they crossed a minefield mined by the extinct Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) guerrilla when they were carrying out coca leaf plantation removal work in the Nukak natural park in the Colombian department of Guaviare.
Standardized-Location: San José del Guaviare, Guaviare, Colombia

Details: Islamic State militants staged an ambush on the Syrian side of the border with Iraq’s western province of Anbar, killing 20 truck drivers.
Five soldiers of the Libyan eastern-based army were killed and seven others wounded in a suicide attack on a military checkpoint in Waddan, Libya.
Two soldiers, including a captain, were killed in a Boko Haram ambush in the Lake Chad region of Chad.
Two soldiers from France’s counter-terrorism force in West Africa were killed and another was hurt when their vehicle struck a landmine in northeast Mali.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: Eight Afghan Local Police personnel manning a check-post have been killed and three others wounded in a Taliban attack in the Dih Yak district of southern Ghazni province.
Boko Haram terrorists killed six people in different attacks in Cameroon's Far North region.
An army man has been injured after terrorists opened fire on a search party in Paribal area of Hajin in Bandipora district of Jammu and Kashmir.
Three people were injured in a roadside bomb attack targeting the car of a senior government official on Peshawar’s Ring Road.
February 2018 Mogadishu attack: At least 45 people were killed and 36 others injured in two car bombings and subsequent gunfire in Mogadishu, Somalia. Five attackers were also killed in the attack.
25 Afghan army members died after Taliban militants attacked their checkpoint in Bala Buluk district of western Farah province. Two Taliban insurgents were also killed in the attack.

One intelligence agency officer was killed and 16 civilians injured when a terrorist detonated a truck bomb in front of a provincial intelligence office in Lashkargah, capital of southern Helmand province.
A militant detonated an explosive-laden hijacked military armored vehicle at an army camp in Nad Ali district, west of Lashkargah, killing two soldiers and injured seven others.
Three people were killed and six others injured in a suicide blast in the Shash Darak area of Kabul.
Rafeullah Gull Afghan, a former senator from Kabul was killed along with his two bodyguards in Kabul city after gunmen opened fire on his vehicle.
At least two policemen have been killed and three others wounded as result of a Taliban attack in central Urozgan province.

Fourteen people were killed and 54 others injured when two car suicide bombers struck the entrance of a military base and a checkpoint near the headquarters of the Southern Transitional Council in Aden. Two other attackers wearing explosive belts also tried to climb over the external gate of the military base to reach the inside but were shot dead by guards before they could blow themselves up.
Two policemen were killed and three wounded in an attack by Islamic State militants on an oil well in Iraq's oil-rich province of Kirkuk.

An attack by dissidents of the former Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) guerrillas, on a police squad in the municipality of Puerto Rico in the department of Meta left one uniformed man dead and another wounded.
At least four people were killed and 13 others injured as a motorbike bomb rocked Yahyakhel district in Afghanistan's eastern Paktika province.
At least four people were killed in two suicide bombings by Boko Haram in the localities of Bourvare and Goumouldi, in the north of Cameroon. Half a dozen others were injured in the attacks.
Three Venezuelans died in the municipality of Tibú, department of Norte de Santander, in an attack by the ELN.
Two Chhattisgarh Armed Force personnel, including an assistant platoon commander, were injured in a blast carried out by Naxalites in Chhattisgarh’s Bijapur district.
A policemen, guarding the residence of the Hurriyat Conference (M) leader, was killed after terrorists attacked him and decamped with his service rifle at Soura in the outskirts of Srinagar.
Terrorists attacked a police guard post at the shrine of Charari Sharief in Budgam district. A constable was killed in the attack.
A suicide bomber blew himself up near the headquarters of Asa’ib Ahel al-Haq in Kirkuk. Three militia members were injured in the attack.

Terrorists opened fire at the security forces in Jammu and Kashmir's Bandipora district. A Lashkar-e-Taiba militant, believed to be from Pakistan, has been killed in an exchange of fire between the terrorists and the security forces.
A Hizbul Mujahideen militant who was in police custody was killed while a police constable was injured in a grenade explosion in a police station in Tral area, Pulwama district.
Three security personnel were injured in an encounter with Naxalites in Chhattisgarh’s Dantewada district.
An armoured vehicle of the Swedish force hit a mine in Soumpi, in the Niafunké cercle. There has been no loss of life.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: Members of the New People's Army ransacked a ranch and abducted six workers, including two off-duty militiamen, in San Francisco, Quezon province.
At least two civilians were killed and four others wounded in a Taliban attack in the Baba Wali area of Nahri Saraj District in Helmand province.

A group of fighters wearing army uniforms kidnapped 30 people, including 19 policemen, after stopping a bus in the Urdo-Balagh locality at the border the provinces of Kandahar and Urozgan. In another incident, a police checkpoint in the Shah Wali Kot district of Kandahar province came under attack by the Taliban fighters leaving six policemen dead and wounding five others.
At least five soldiers were killed and 13 wounded in a bomb attack against a Colombian army caravan in a rural area of the city of Cucuta, bordering Venezuela.
Three civilians lost their lives in an attack carried out by Islamic State terrorists on the outskirts of Karashabak village in Sinjar district.
A vehicle of the armed forces hit an improvised explosive device about 7 km east of Dioura in the Ségou region. Six soldiers were killed in the blast.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: A terrorist killed a water and forestry officer with a gun in Douentza, Mali.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: Two soldiers were killed and two others wounded when a suicide bomber drove into their patrol vehicle in the Lake Chad region of Nigeria.
Five soldiers and three civilians were wounded in an ambush by members of the New People’s Army in General Luna, Quezon province.
Two people were killed and three others injured as Taliban militants ambushed a patrol team of pro-government militias in the Khwaja Sabz Posh district of Faryab province.
Terrorists opened fire upon a civilian in Tral area in South Kashmir's Pulwama district. The citizen has been critically wounded.
Four UN peacekeepers have been killed and four more were wounded after their vehicle hit an explosive device in Mali's central Mopti region.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: A suicide bombing killed four members of Pakistan's paramilitary force and injured eight others on the outskirts of the southwestern city of Quetta while elsewhere in the city, gunmen opened fire on a senior police officer's convoy, killing two of his guards.
A new assault by the ELN with gunfire and cylinder bombs, which was registered in the rural area of Convención, killed one soldier and injured four others.
Two Iraqi soldiers were killed and three others injured in an attack by the Islamic State in Badush, Nineveh province.
Boko Haram insurgents shot a woman and abducted three people in the Madagali Local Government Area of Adamawa state.

Boko Haram militants killed at least 11 people including three aid workers in an attack on a military barracks in the town of Rann in Borno state. Another three aid workers were wounded and one more kidnapped.

At least three people were killed and three others wounded when a suicide car bomb blast targeted a security checkpoint in Sinka Dher on the outskirts of the Somali capital Mogadishu. Another three people were killed and two injured in a mortar attack in the Somali capital Mogadishu.
Five Peshmerga fighters were wounded and a shepherd was killed in an attack by Islamic State militants in Kifri, Iraq.
Five police officers have been killed and three others injured after al-Shabab militants attacked two security camps in Kenya's northeastern Mandera county.
Part of: Spillover of the war in Somalia

Details: A foreign forces convoy was hit by a suicide car bomb attack in the ninth police district of Kabul, killing three people and injuring 22 others.
2018 Ouagadougou attacks: 30 people were killed and 85 wounded in terrorist attacks on the French embassy and cultural center in Burkina Faso and the country’s army headquarters.
A female suicide bomber blew up herself at a mosque in the Fulatari area of Buni Yadi, Gujba Local Government Area of Yobe state, killing seven persons and injuring 28 others.
Twelve Naxalites and a constable of the elite commando force Greyhounds were killed in an encounter in the forests of Chhattisgarh’s Bijapur district. Three others were injured in the incident.

A suicide bomber rammed his explosives-laden minibus into a military camp in Afgooye, a district in Lower Shabelle region, killing at least 5 Somali soldiers and wounding several others. Six other government soldiers died after a remote-controlled landmine targeted a convoy carrying injured soldiers from Afgooye to Mogadishu.

At least three Burundian soldiers of the African Union Mission to Somalia were killed in an Al-Shabaab attack near Jowhar, Somalia. Seven others were injured, four were missing, and one armoured vehicle and four trucks were damaged during the attack.
Two policemen were killed in an attack with explosives on the road from Caldono to Siberia in the department of Cauca.

Location: Beni Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Six people were shot dead and another was stabbed to death in a raid by Ugandan Islamist rebels in the village of Eringeti in Democratic Republic of Congo's North Kivu province.
Standardized-Location: Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: Two soldiers, a border guard and a civilian were lightly injured in a car-ramming attack in the northern Israeli city of Acre. The driver of the car was shot multiple times and critically wounded.
A Shia Muslim youth was killed in an attack by Islamic State terrorists in Quetta, provincial capital city of Balochistan province.
Naxalites torched several vehicles and killed a former cop in Sukma district of south Chhattisgarh.
Four security men, including a captain, were killed in a shooting with Islamic State militants in Mosul City.
A landmine exploded after a military vehicle carrying border guards hit it in Ar-Rutbah town in western Anbar province. Three people were injured as a result of the explosion.

One policeman was killed and three others were wounded in a bomb attack on their vehicle in the western Anbar province. Another bomb exploded near the borders between Iraq and Saudi Arabia, leaving two personnel wounded.
Insurgents attacked two farmers on their farm and slit their throats in the village of Gudda in Mafa Local Government Area of Borno state.

A team of loggers were attacked by Boko Haram while on their way to the bush to collect firewood in the state of Borno. Three loggers were killed in the attack, while the rest fled to Dikwa and left behind a pickup van.
A suicide bomber on a bicycle killed three people when he detonated his explosives on the outskirts of the northeast Nigerian city of Maiduguri.
A rifleman of 13 Sikh Light Infantry was killed in an encounter with the National Socialist Council of Nagaland at Khoupum area in Manipur's Noney district.

Location: Beni Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Twenty people people were killed in several attacks in the province of North Kivu in the Democratic Republic of Congo. More than 15 others were reported missing after the attacks and probably kidnapped by the attackers.
Standardized-Location: Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: At least two people were killed and three others injured in an oil tanker explosion caused by a bomb in the Bihsud district of Nangarhar province.
One person was killed and two others injured after a landmine left behind by terrorists exploded on the outskirts of Arsal.
Part of: Spillover of the Syrian Civil War

Details: Four loggers were killed when they stepped on a landmine left by Boko Haram near Dikwa, 90 km east of the Borno state capital, Maiduguri.
Three people were killed in an attack in Gamboru on the border with Cameroon.
A civilian was killed and five others were wounded when a bomb-laden vehicle exploded in the Syrian city of Al-Bab in the Aleppo governorate.
A suicide bomber killed three people, including the local head of the Ministry of Hajj and Religious Affairs, and injured 16 others in Jalalabad, the capital of Nangarhar province.

Heavily armed terrorists attacked a district police headquarters in the Spin Boldak district of southern Kandahar. Three attackers and four police officers were killed and three others injured in the attack.
A car bomb attack killed nine people and injured more than 60 others in Jarabulus, Syria.
A civilian was killed in an attack by PKK terrorists in the Besta district of Şirnak province.
Two civilians were wounded in a bomb blast in the north of Diyala province.
Jihadists attacked and set fire to the construction site of a dam in central Mali, near the town of Djenné in the Mopti region.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: One person was shot dead and another injured by terrorists in Killi Chakar Khan area near Sariab Road, Quetta.

At least seventeen security forces, including ten local policemen and seven army soldiers, were killed after the Taliban militants attacked a security post in the Khwaja Ghar district of northern Takhar province. Thirteen others, including nine local police officers, were wounded in the attack.
A suicide bomber killed 10 people and injured 22 others when he set off explosives in a crowd of Shiite Muslims near a mosque complex in Kabul.
At least 24 members of the Afghan security forces were killed and several others injured in a Taliban attack in the Balu Buluk district of western Farah province.
A suicide car bombing has killed at least three security personnel at a checkpoint on the outskirts of the northeastern Libyan city of Ajdabiya.
Four Malian soldiers were killed and two others seriously injured when their vehicle ran over a mine in the central town of Dialloubé as they returned from an operation against jihadists.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: At least four members of the Somali security force were killed and another injured in a remote-controlled improvised explosive device attack on the outskirts of Mogadishu.
Seven policemen were killed in a Taliban attack in the Zurmat district of Paktia province. An eighth policeman was injured in the attack.
Four local policemen were killed and seven others wounded after Taliban militants attacked their outpost in the Ali Abad district of northern Kunduz province.

Seven civilians, including two women and three children, were killed and two others wounded when Taliban struck their vehicle with a rocket in the Bati Kot district of the eastern Afghan province of Nangarhar.
A group of armed terrorists hurled a grenade at the residence of a Peoples Democratic Party legislator in Jammu and Kashmir' s Kulgam district. No casualties were reported.

Four terrorists were killed after infiltrating Iran and attacking a military check post near the city of Saravan in the province of Sistan and Baluchestan. Two members of the Basiji paramilitary forces, affiliated with the Revolutionary Guards, were wounded in the fight, during which one of the attackers was killed after detonating an explosive vest.
Two farmers were killed after an explosive charge left over by Islamic State militants went off in Hawija district of Kirkuk province.

Islamic State terrorists, who had set up a fake roadblock on a major road, have killed 15 people and injured 5 others in Kirkuk province. In a separate attack, three people were killed while driving a car further north near the city of Daquq. The attackers then burned the car.
Al-Shabaab assailants have shot and killed at least three people in Mogadishu, the Somali capital.
Two police officers were injured in a donkey bomb attack in the Sirkanay district of Kunar province, on the border with Pakistan.
In a village of Saladin governorate, seven people, including the mayor, were killed by armed men in military uniforms. Three others were injured in the attack.
Two soldiers were wounded in an explosion caused by a bomb that was placed by Islamic state militants near the Fallujah dam in Anbar province.
At least one soldier was killed and several others were wounded in Mogadishu in a shootout between Somali security forces and Al-Shabaab militants.
Two children from the same family died in an explosion of a landmine planted by Islamic state militants in the town of Gharanij in Deir ez-Zor governorate.
Five police officers were killed and two others injured in a Taliban attack on a check post in Farah City, the capital of western Farah.
Three police officers were killed and another injured in an attack on a police station in Goubé in the Tillabéri region of Niger.

2018 Sukma attack: Nine paramilitary troopers of the Indian Central Reserve Police Force were killed and about ten others wounded after Naxalites targeted their vehicle with an improvised explosive device in Sukma district of the Central Indian state of Chhattisgarh.
A bomb blast targeted Palestinian prime minister Rami Hamdallah’s convoy during a visit to the Gaza Strip, leaving seven people hurt.

Location: Beni Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: Three civilians were killed in an attack by terrorists of the Allied Democratic Forces on the Beni - Kasindi road in the Beni territory of North Kivu province. Two attackers were also killed in the incident.
Standardized-Location: Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: At least 10 people were killed and 30 others injured in a suicide car bombing that hit a supply post belonging to a Yemeni security force backed by the United Arab Emirates in the southern port city of Aden, Yemen.
At least seven security personnel were killed and seven others injured in a Taliban attack in Farah City, the capital of the western province of Farah.
At least two Afghan police personnel were killed and three others injured after a suicide car bombing struck a border police outpost in the Nad Ali district of southern Helmand province.
At least ten people were killed and 35 others injured in a suicide bombing that targeted a police check post in Raiwind on the outskirts of Lahore, Pakistan.
Two people, including a woman, were shot dead by Naxalites in a village of Seraikela Kharsawan district in Jharkhand.
At least two Puntland bomb disposal experts were killed in a roadside bomb explosion in the Galgala Mountains of Bari region.
A water and forestry officer was killed by terrorists who attacked a post in the locality of Nassougou in the east of Burkina Faso. The attackers also set the buildings and a vehicle on fire.
Seven Iraqi soldiers were killed, while seven others were wounded in an armed attack by Islamic State militants, west of Anbar.
At least three people were killed and two others injured in a grenade attack in Bosaso, the commercial city of Somalia’s northeastern Puntland region.

Terrorists tried to snatch the service rifle of a personal security officer of a BJP worker in Khanmoh's Balhama area in Pulwama district, India. They failed in the bid and fled, but Khan's personal security officer was injured in the skirmish. In an ensuing encounter, one CRPF trooper sustained injuries and three terrorists were killed.

Two Israeli soldiers were killed and three others injured after a Palestinian drove his vehicle into them outside the Mevo Dothan settlement in the northern West Bank. The attacker was captured by Israeli security forces shortly after the attack and was lightly injured.
Four Iraqi soldiers were killed and four others injured in an armed attack launched by Islamic State militants on a security checkpoint located on a highway in Al-Qa'im district, west of Anbar.
At least three people were killed and four others injured in a suicide car bombing that targeted a foreign security company in the Afghan capital Kabul.
Two children were killed and 17 others injured in a bomb blast in the Nadir Shah Kot District of southeastern Khost Province.
A roadside bomb killed a young shepherd and wounded five others in the western province of Ghor in Afghanistan.
Five police personnel were killed and four others wounded after Taliban militants attacked security checkpoints in Afghanistan's eastern province of Ghazni.
Terrorists attacked a convoy of police officials in South Kashmir’s Shopian district. No one was hurt in the exchange of fire.

Terrorists killed two polio workers and seriously wounded two others in Safi tehsil of Mohmand Agency. The gunmen also attacked tribal police and the paramilitary Frontier Corps when they responded to the attack, killing one paramilitary and wounding another.

An attacker dressed in a school uniform set off a grenade in a group of hundreds of university students in Afghanistan’s capital, killing himself and wounding six students. The assailant, who slipped past two guards, was wearing an explosives vest that didn't explode.
A terrorist stabbed an Israeli man to death in the Muslim Quarter of Jerusalem’s Old City. The attacker was shot dead at the scene by an Israel Police officer.
A group of armed men, believed to be members of the Islamic State, attacked a village in the town of al-Riyad in Hawija district, killing five civilians, including a woman.
At least three Yemeni soldiers backed by the United Arab Emirates were killed and another injured in an ambush by Al-Qaeda militants in the Mudiyah district of Abyan province.
At least four people were killed and eleven others injured in a motorcycle bombing in Jalalabad in the Afghan province of Nangarhar.
One civilian was killed and nine others wounded when a motorcycle bomb went off at a bazaar in Shindand district center.
Two villagers were killed and three others injured in an ambush by Islamic state militants near the village of al-Heleiwat in the town of al Zab, west of Kirkuk.
A security officer was killed, while two others were wounded in an ambush by Islamic state militants near a checkpoint in al-Dibis town, northwest Kirkuk province.
Islamic state insurgents killed two persons and kidnapped three others after they set up a fake checkpoint in a village in the Hawija district of Kirkuk province.
An Iraqi woman was killed and another injured when a bomb placed by Islamic state militants exploded in the village of Albu Bali, east of Ramadi.
Four policemen, including an officer, were killed in an attack launched by Islamic state militants in the Nineveh governorate.
Six people were killed and 15 others injured when a convoy containing at least two families was attacked at a non-governmental checkpoint between Tuz Khurmatu and Daquq.
A man with a firearm attacked and injured a police officer in the Chechen capital Grozny. The assailant was killed.
At least 44 people, most of them women and children, were killed when terrorists attacked with rockets on a busy market in Damascus. 35 others were wounded in the attack.

Five security personnel, including three Army jawans and two policemen, and five militants were killed in a shooting in the Halmatpora area of Kupwara district. Another special police officer was injured in the exchange of fire.
March 2018 Kabul suicide bombing: A suicide bombing near a Shiite shrine in Kabul killed at least 33 people and injured 65 others as Afghans celebrated the Persian New Year.
Seven Iraqi border guards were killed in an ambush by Islamic State extremists near the town of Ar-Rutbah in the western Iraqi province of Anbar. Two drivers were also killed in the attack.
Islamic state extremists kidnapped four Iraqi officers in the province of Kirkuk in Iraq.
At least 18 people were killed and 22 others wounded in a car bomb explosion near a hotel in in the Somali capital Mogadishu.

Carcassonne and Trèbes attack: A gunman affiliated with the Islamic State attacked the French cities of Carcassonne and Trèbes: He attacked and stole a car, killing the passenger and wounding the driver, in Carcassonne. He arrived in Trèbes and during the process a police officer was injured when the terrorist shot him. Then, he attacked a supermarket, where two civilians were killed and several others injured. A policeman exchanged himself for a hostage, was later shot and stabbed and died of his injuries in hospital. The attacker was later killed by the police.
At least 20 people were killed and 55 more injured in a suicide car bomb attack at the Ghazi Muhammad Ayub Khan stadium during a wrestling match in Lashkargah, Afghanistan.
A bomb placed under a car exploded in Egypt's second largest city Alexandria, killing two people, including a policeman. The bombing, which wounded five others, targeted Alexandria's security chief.
Five District Reserve Guard jawans were injured in a bomb blast carried out by Naxalites in Chhattisgarh's Sukma district.
Seven people were killed and 25 others injured in a car bomb explosion in central Idlib in northwestern Syria.
A bomb exploded near a protest site in the Afghan capital Kabul, killing one person and wounding 13 others.
Twenty-four people were injured after a hand grenade was hurled towards the stage of a spring festival in Dera Ismail Khan.
Standardized-Location: Dera Ismāīl Khān, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Pakistan (Dera Ismail Khan)

Details: Eight Iraqi policemen who were kidnapped on the Kirkuk - Baghdad road were shot and killed by Islamic state militants.

Islamic State militants opened fire on a civilian car on a road in the east of the town of Al-Sadiyah, some 120 km northeast of the Iraqi capital Baghdad. Four people were killed in the attack, including a woman and a child, and two others were injured.
Islamic State members set up an armed ambush near the village of Dugheila, located between the towns of al-Riyad and Hawija, which killed five personnel of Hashd al-Shaabi.
A bomb blast near a market in the Al-Mushahad region of Al-Tarmia district killed one citizen and injured two others.
Islamic state militants blew up a Sufi shrine in Daquq district of Kirkuk province.
Two suicide bombers attacked a Shiite mosque in Herat, killing three, including the two terrorists, and wounding nine others.

Location: Beni Territory, Democratic Republic of Congo
Details: One soldier was killed and another seriously injured in an attack by Allied Democratic Forces militants in Kokola in the Beni territory of North Kivu province.
Standardized-Location: Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: A terrorist was killed and a teenage girl sustained bullet wounds in an encounter in Arizal area of Beerwah in central Kashmir's Budgam district.
At least four people were killed and ten others injured in a suicide car bomb attack near Somalia's parliament headquarters in Mogadishu.
Taliban militants destroyed a major electricity tower with a bomb in Baghlan province in northern Afghanistan, disrupting imported power supply to five provinces, including Kabul.
A Naxalite was killed and two Central Reserve Police Force personnel were injured in an ambush in Chhattisgarh's Sukma district.
Terrorists attacked soldiers in the Kachdora area of Shopian district in southern Kashmir. No one was injured in the incident.
Three people, including two Iraqi mayors, were killed and one woman injured in separate armed attacks by Islamic state militants in Diyala province.
A Somali lawmaker was shot dead by Al-Shabaab assassins in her home in Mogadishu, Somalia.
Two people were stabbed to death and five others injured by a radical Islamist in a mosque in the eastern Sudanese city of Kassala. The attacker was later killed by worshippers.
Islamic State militants killed a tribal fighter and injured three other fighters in an attack in Kirkuk province.
At least 10 people are dead and 10 others are missing after militants attacked outlying areas of the eastern city of Beni. A terrorist from the Ugandan Allied Democratic Forces was also killed.
Standardized-Location: Beni, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Details: Two civilians were wounded when a bomb exploded under the rubble of one of the houses in the center of Ramadi in Anbar province.
At least 12 Yemeni soldiers were killed after Al-Qaida gunmen ambushed a military convoy in the southeastern province of Hadhramaut.
A special police officer was shot dead in his house by terrorists in South Kashmir’s Bijbehara, Anantnag district. His wife sustained multiple injuries.
Terrorists fired on a security patrol near Ahagam in the Shopian district in southern Kashmir. A Hizbul Mujahideen militant was injured in the shooting.
Terrorists shot at and injured a teacher in South Kashmir’s Kulgam district.
At least five Iraqi security personnel were killed in an ambush by Islamic State terrorists in the city of Mosul.
Two Iraqi civilians were killed when an explosive device exploded in their home in Rawa, Anbar province.
At least eight people, including civilians, were killed and eleven others injured in a suicide car bombing that hit a security checkpoint in the eastern Libyan city of Ajdabiya.
A member of the provincial council of Kunar and a religious scholar were killed in a suicide bombing in the Watapur district of Kunar province. A security guard was also wounded in the attack.
A Central Reserve Police Force jawan was injured in the explosion of a pressure bomb, planted by Naxalites, in Bijapur district of Chhattisgarh.
Three policemen were killed while another five were injured when an improvised explosive device that targeted the district police officer's convoy in Dera Ismail Khan exploded.
Standardized-Location: Dera Ismāīl Khān, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Pakistan (Dera Ismail Khan)

Details: Six Turkish village guards were killed in an attack by PKK terrorists in Siirt’s Eruh district. Three village guards and four soldiers were wounded in the attack.
At least five people, including four suicide bombers, were killed and 13 others injured when terrorists attacked Muna Zawuya in the Mafa Local Government Area of Borno state.
Three people were killed and 25 injured in a suicide bombing by an Islamic state terrorist in the Tooz district in the Iraqi province of Saladin.
Terrorists shot and injured a special police officer while he was on duty in the Khanabal Chowk area of Anantnag district.
A special police officer was shot dead by terrorists in Jammu and Kashmir's Pulwama district.

One security personnel was killed, while a terrorist was also killed in an exchange of fire during an intelligence-based operation in Balochistan’s Mastung district. Two more terrorists were wounded in the incident.

Location: Shopian district and Anantnag district, India
Details: In three anti-terrorist operations, three members of the army and 13 terrorists were killed in the districts of Shopian and Anantnag in South Kashmir. Several others were injured in the encounters.
A civilian was wounded in a car bomb explosion in southwest Baghdad.

2018 African Union base attack in Bulo Marer: Al-Shabaab terrorists attacked an African Union military camp in the Bulo Marer area of Lower Shebelle, where Ugandan peacekeepers are stationed, killing at least 59 people. 14 militants died in the attack.
In a targeted killing incident, one member of the Shia Hazara community was killed and another was injured when gunmen opened fire on their vehicle in Quetta's Kandahari Bazaar area.
Boko Haram fighters attacked a military base and two surrounding villages near the Nigerian city of Maiduguri in the Jere Local Government Area, killing at least 20 people and wounding 84.
A bomb went off in the Al-Tin district in Al-Qa' im, in the west of Anbar province, killing one person and injuring two others.
Four children were wounded when a bomb exploded outside a medical complex in the town of Bartella, east of Mosul.
At least four people were killed in an attack targeting Christians in the southwestern Pakistani city of Quetta. Three others, including a 12-year-old girl, were also injured in the incident.
Terrorists kidnapped a civilian and injured three of his relatives in Jammu and Kashmir's Bandipora district. Later, the person kidnapped by the gunmen was found dead.
Hundreds of Taliban fighters attacked the center of the Almar district in the north of Faryab province and killed two policemen.
At least two Afghan soldiers were killed and five others injured after Taliban fighters attacked a security forces' camp in Khas Urozgan district in Afghanistan.

Anti-balaka fighters attacked a UN peacekeeping base in Tagbara in the Central African Republic, killing one Mauritanian peacekeeper and injuring 11 others. 22 Anti-balaka fighters died in the shootout.
