A police officer was shot and killed in Narathiwat's Su-ngai Padi district.
Six Afghan National Army soldiers were wounded when two bombs exploded in Kabul.
Lashkar-e-Taiba militants kidnapped a man and his son from the Bandipora district in northern Kashmir, the man escaped with gunshot wounds. Later the headless body of the son was found in an orchard.
Islamic state militants attacked a vehicle carrying civilians in the Khanaqin district of Iraq's Diyala province and killed three people on board.
A Saudi soldier was killed in a raid against militants in the city of Al-Awamiyah in the eastern province of Qatif in Saudi Arabia.
18 Tatmadaw soldiers were killed and 13 injured when armed rebels attacked a Tatmadaw's Battalion 86 military base in Hpakant Township.

An explosive device in a car exploded behind a mosque in northeast Damascus, killing one civilian and injuring six others. Five civilians were killed and 30 others injured in another terrorist attack with mortar grenades by Jaysh al-Islam terrorists in Damascus.
At least six people, including two soldiers, were killed and three others injured in two suicide car bombings in the Somali capital Mogadishu.
A Taliban attack in Arghandab district in Zabul province in southern Afghanistan killed at least four police officers. Two others were injured in the incident.
At least two soldiers of the Afghan National Army were killed and five others injured in a Taliban attack on a check post in the village of Balghali in Sar-e Pol city.
Two armed men opened fire on a MINUSMA vehicle in the city of Gao in northern Mali. A peacekeeper sitting in the vehicle succumbed to his injuries when he was taken to hospital.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: Two suicide bombings targeting a political party headquarters in the city of Hīt killed five people and injured eleven more.
Ten civilians were killed and 20 others injured when a car bomb exploded near a mosque in the city of Al-Bab in northern Syria.
Eight civilians were killed and 37 others injured in several mortar attacks in Damascus.
Six security forces were killed and three others injured when Islamic State and Taliban fighters jointly attacked a check post in a village in Sar-e Pol city.
Six Iraqi soldiers were injured in a suicide bombing in the city of Hīt in the western province of Anbar.
A village defence volunteer was shot dead while riding his motorcycle in the Mayo district of Pattani province.
Armed men assassinated the mayor of Koutougou, a commune in northern Burkina Faso.
At least eight civilians were killed and 21 others injured in a bomb explosion in Shindand in the western province of Herat.
At least seven people were injured when a suicide bomber blew himself up near a Balochistan Frontier Corps vehicle in Quetta.
Three motorcycle bombs exploded in the border town of Su-ngai Kolok in the Narathiwat province of Thailand, injuring at least 13 people.

Maoists triggered two improvised explosive devices and fired at a Central Reserve Police Force patrol on the Bijapur-Bhopalpatnam road. No one was injured in the attack. In another attack, an IED planted by Maoists hit a bus in which 30 security personnel were travelling. Two security personnel of the District Reserve Group were killed, while six others were critically injured.
A District Voluntary Force trooper died in a landmine explosion triggered by Maoists in Muniguda.
Two Muslim insurgents ambushed a police unit in Yarang district of Pattani province and injured three police officers. They were killed in the gunfight.
Four paramilitary personnel were wounded in an attack by Islamic State militants on a training facility in the city of Balad, south of Tikrit.

Fourteen people, including a district governor, were killed in a Taliban attack in the Khwaja Umari district of the southeastern province of Ghazni in Afghanistan. In addition, five people were injured.
Taliban militants ambushed a convoy of Afghan security backup forces in Ghazni, killing six policemen and injuring three others.
Terrorists threw a grenade at the police station in Pulwama, injuring two policemen.
25 people were killed and 18 wounded when explosives exploded at a funeral for Sunni Muslim tribal fighters in the northern Iraqi city of Al-Shirqat.

Four Iraqi policemen were wounded in an attack by Islamic state militants in Kirkuk province. Earlier, Islamic state fighters killed a man in front of his family, torched and blew up houses of other civilians in the same province.
Three people were killed in a landmine explosion on the outskirts of the north-eastern Lebanese border town of Arsal.
Part of: Spillover of the Syrian Civil War

Details: A car bomb exploded in the city of Azaz in northern Syria, killing 6 people and injuring 10 others.

One student was killed and others were injured by terrorists who attacked a school in Bouro in the department of Nassoumbou while shouting "Allahu Akbar". The attackers kidnapped a teacher and headed towards the neighbouring commune of Ariel.
At least five people were killed and another twelve injured in a bomb attack on a football stadium in the town of Barawa in the Lower Shabelle region of Somalia.
One civilian was killed and another injured when a bomb exploded in Al-Shirqat district in Saladin province.
A district police chief was killed in a Taliban attack in the capital of the southern province of Kandahar. His bodyguard was wounded in the attack.

In Sancharak district, in the northern province of Sar-i-Pul, two government checkpoints in the west were attacked by Taliban fighters with night vision devices and sniper rifles, initially killing a security guard. When local pro-government militiamen tried to counter the assault, they fell into a Taliban ambush and 10 more were killed.
In the province of Faryab in northern Afghanistan, the Taliban killed four government defenders by shooting them in the head.
Militants wearing explosive belts blew themselves up as they tried to infiltrate a military base in Egypt's central Sinai, killing 30 soldiers and injuring 40 others.
One person died and two others were injured in a train accident in Lakhisarai, Bihar. The accident was caused by Naxalites.

Maoists abducted an engineer in the Sukma district. Later he was found dead. The terrorists also set a truck on fire and triggered three bombs in a vacant camp of the Central Reserve Police Force in the same area.

The attackers first fired rockets at a camp of MINUSMA and Barkhane in Timbuktu, Mali. Then two car bombs, suicide vehicles, were detonated at various locations in the camp. One peacekeeper was killed, 15 terrorists were killed, 15 French soldiers and 19 Malian soldiers were injured in the attack.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: Two Afghan Local Police checkpoints in the Jaghatū district of Ghazni Province were attacked, killing eight officers and injuring four others.
Terrorists shot and injured a man in South Kashmir's Shopian District.
Two Christians were killed and eight others injured in a shooting outside a church in Quetta, the provincial capital of Balochistan province.
A civilian and a policeman were injured in the Shopian district of Jammu and Kashmir when terrorists opened fire on a police party.
A vehicle of the Malian armed forces hit a mine 25 km from Sokolo in Niono Cercle, Ségou region, during a mission. 8 soldiers were wounded, 2 of them seriously.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: At least three soldiers were killed in action, another was injured following a terror attack by the PKK in the southeastern Turkish province of Şırnak.
Six ethnic Hazaras were shot and killed by gunmen in Afghanistan's western Ghor province. Four other civilians were wounded in the incident.
Islamic state fighters beheaded a 12-year-old boy in Darzab district in the northern Afghan province of Jowzjan.
Three IEC voter registration employees and two policemen were abducted by the Taliban in Chaghcharan, the center of Ghor province.
Terrorists opened fire on the Shopian Police Station in Shopian in Jammu and Kashmir. No one was killed or injured in the incident.
Terrorists opened fire on an army patrol in Pulwama's town of Tral in southern Kashmir. One soldier suffered bullet wounds following the attack.
Terrorists attacked a border post in the city of Mirjaveh, killing two Iranian border guards, two Basiji forces and injuring three others. Two attackers were also killed in the ambush.
Five Iraqi soldiers were injured in a bomb attack south of Baqubah, the capital of the Iraqi province of Diyala.
Five people, including a border police commander, were killed and three policemen wounded when a sticky bomb attached to the commander's vehicle exploded in the city of Kandahar.

A car bomb exploded in the eastern Libyan city of Benghazi, killing one civilian and injuring three others. The bombing targeted Field Marshal Khalifa Haftar's chief of staff, but he escaped unharmed.
A shopkeeper belonging to the Shia Hazara community was killed in a shooting in Quetta.
At least four Somali soldiers were killed and several others injured in an ambush by Al-Shabaab near the town of Balad, some 31 km northeast of Mogadishu.

Islamic state militants launched an attack in the Mayadin region in the southeast of the Syrian province of Deir ez-Zor and killed 25 Syrian government forces. At least 13 militants were also killed in the attack.
A roadside bomb killed five people and injured 14 others in the Haska Meyna district of Nangarhar province.
An officer of the Central Reserve Police Force was killed in a shooting with Maoists in a dense forest in the Sukma district of Chhattisgarh.
Taliban insurgents attacked Chahar Bolak district in Balkh province, killing two people and injuring seven others.
A Boko Haram militant and a soldier were killed in a shooting in Gamboru in the state of Borno in Nigeria.

22 April 2018 Kabul suicide bombing: A suicide bomb attack at a voter registration centre in the Afghan capital Kabul killed at least 69 people and injured 120 others. The casualties were all civilians, most of whom had been waiting outside the office to apply for their IDs in order to register to vote in the upcoming elections.
Three brothers were beheaded by Islamic State militants in Chaparhar district in Nangarhar province in Afghanistan.
Nine Afghan National Army soldiers were killed after Taliban militants attacked a security checkpoint on the outskirts of Qala i Naw in Badghis province.
Seven Afghan National Police personnel died when Taliban fighters attacked a security checkpoint in the Qadis district of Badghis province.
Homemade rockets were fired at the UN and French military bases in the city of Timbuktu in northern Mali. No one was injured in the attack.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: Boko Haram jihadists shot dead 18 forest workers who had been collecting firewood in Borno State, near the town of Gamboru, on the border with Cameroon. In another incident, a vehicle carrying civilians travelling in a nearby army convoy hit a mine placed by insurgents, killing three people and wounding eleven others near the village of Wumbi.
Gunmen on a motorcycle killed two Shiites and wounded a third on the outskirts of the capital of Balochistan province, Quetta.
Taliban fighters kidnapped four passengers of a commuter bus which allegedly had left Ghor province for Herat. The incident occurred in the Chishti Sharif district.
A Border Security Force trooper was injured in an exchange of fire with Naxalites in Chhattisgarh's Kanker district.
Two workers and a driver were killed in a landmine explosion in the Nabarangpur district of Odisha.

Four Jaish-e-Mohammad terrorists were killed in an encounter in Tral in Pulwama district in southern Kashmir. A soldier and a policeman were killed and two soldiers were seriously injured in the shooting.
At least eight policemen were killed and 23 others injured in three suicide bombings targeting security personnel in Quetta, the provincial capital of Balochistan.

Terrorists attacked a political worker in Rajpora in the Pulwama district of southern Kashmir when he was travelling in his vehicle and killed him on the spot. Two of his security forces were injured and hospitalized.
The deputy governor of the central Afghan province of Logar and his two bodyguards were killed in a Taliban ambush in Waghjan. The governor's spokesman was injured in the attack.
Two policemen and a civilian were injured after terrorists threw a grenade at a police station in Kulgam.
A CRPF patrol was attacked by a group of terrorists, killing a civilian in Jammu and Kashmir's Anantnag district.
At least four people were killed and 32 others injured when a hand grenade was hurled at a wedding ceremony in a villagei in North Waziristan.

Six people, including three civilians, a member of the Civilian Joint Task Force and two suicide bombers, were killed and nine others injured in an attack by Boko Haram insurgents in the Nigerian city of Maiduguri. Later another suicide bomber attacked an armored van of the Federal Special Anti-Robbery Squad in the same area, injuring two police officers.
At least 47 people were killed and two injured in two armed attacks on the settlements of Aklaz and Awakassa in the Ménaka region of Mali.
Part of: Northern Mali conflict, Insurgency in the Maghreb

Details: A suicide bomber in a minivan attacked a military base in the Nad Ali district of Helmand province in southern Afghanistan and killed four civilians and two soldiers. Three civilians and two soldiers were also wounded in the attack.
A total of 12 people were injured when a bomb explosion in the city of Jalalabad, the capital of the eastern province of Nangarhar in Afghanistan, hit a booth of police traffic.
One sub-engineer, two construction workers were kidnapped and six vehicles were set on fire by Naxalites in Chhattisgarh's Balrampur district.
Two people from the ethnic Hazara community were shot dead at their shop in a busy shopping area of Quetta, the capital of Balochistan.
At least seven people, including three senior military officials, were killed and eight others injured in a suicide bombing in the city of Galkayo in central Somalia.
Remains of explosives belonging to the Taliban group exploded in the Surkh-Rōd district in the eastern province of Nangarhar in Afghanistan, killing three people and injuring eight others.
At least seven people, including children and policemen, were injured in a bomb attack near a voter registration center in Jalalabad, the capital of the eastern Afghan province of Nangarhar.
A Commando Battalion for Resolute Action soldier was injured after Naxalites triggered a bomb explosion in Chhattisgarh's Dantewada district.
A BJP worker was shot and injured by terrorists in Srinagar.
At least three soldiers were killed in an attack by Boko Haram militants in the Diffa region in southeast Niger.
A senior police officer was killed and four others injured in two bomb explosions in Bihsud district in the eastern province of Nangarhar in Afghanistan.
30 April 2018 Kabul suicide bombings: At least 29 people were killed and 50 others injured in two suicide bombings in the Afghan capital Kabul, including several journalists documenting the scene.
At least 11 students were killed and 16 other people, including five Romanian soldiers, were injured in a suicide car bombing in Daman district in the southern province of Kandahar.
Two Hizbul Mujahideen fighters were killed and three army personnel, including a Major, wounded in an encounter in the village of Drabgam in Kashmir's Pulwama district.
Three boys were shot and killed by Lashkar-e-Taiba terrorists in the old town of Baramulla in Jammu and Kashmir.
Two people were killed and a third injured when a roadside bomb hit a civilian vehicle in the capital of the central Logar province in Afghanistan.

Gunmen armed with grenades attacked the Notre-Dame de Fatima church in Bangui, the capital of the Central African Republic, during mass, killing 24 people, including a priest, and injuring 170 others.
Extremists linked to the Islamic state group killed at least 17 people, including elderly persons, who were burned alive in their homes, in Tindinbawen and Taylalene in the Ménaka region of Mali.

2018 Mubi suicide bombings: At least 86 people were killed in two suicide attacks at a mosque and a market in Mubi, a town in the state of Adamawa in northeastern Nigeria. 58 others were injured in the bombings.

In the Russian city of Neftekumsk, a man attacked two police officers with a knife. As a result, both law enforcement officers were injured. During the arrest, the man resisted and stabbed one of the policemen, after which a policeman shot him dead.
A United Nations World Health Organization worker was shot dead in Somalia's capital Mogadishu.
Islamic state militants dressed in Iraqi military uniforms attacked Al Tarmia north of Baghdad, killing 21 members of a local tribe that was a vocal opponent of the extremists and injuring 13 others.
Terrorists hurled a petrol bomb at a lawmaker's residence in Jammu and Kashmir's Shopian district. No casualties were reported.
An explosive device placed under a car went off, killing a man and his two sisters in the Diyala province in Iraq.
A civilian was killed in a bomb explosion in the Dibis district of Kirkuk province in Iraq.
Islamic state militants attacked the Iraqi police in the town of Jalawla, resulting in at least two deaths and seven injuries among police ranks.

2018 attack on the High National Elections Commission in Tripoli, Libya: Suicide bombers attacked the head offices of Libya's electoral commission in Tripoli, killing at least 16 people, injuring 20 and setting fire to the building.
A roadside bomb exploded, but did not cause any casualties in the Safi tehsil of Mohmand Agency in Pakistan.
A landmine placed by Islamic state militants killed three children and injured seven more in the south of Al-Hasakah near a garbage dump.
Boko Haram militants attacked the village of Auno in the Konduga local government area. No life was lost, but a vehicle was burned by the terrorists.
Three security personnel were injured in a bomb explosion in the Jani Khel area of Bannu district in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province.
At least two people were killed and 18 injured, some of them seriously, in an attack on a vehicle carrying civilian employees of a security agency in Attock.
Six people were killed and eight others injured in a car bomb explosion in the town of Al-Dana in the northwestern province of Idlib in Syria.
At least four people were killed and nine others injured when four suicide bombers attacked Mainari Shuwa and neighbouring Mainari Kanuri in the Konduga local government area of Borno state.
Six labourers were killed and one injured in a shooting in Balochistan's Kharan district.
Terrorists hurled a grenade at a police station in Pulwama, Jammu and Kashmir. The grenade exploded outside the police station and no one was injured in the incident.
A 35-year-old man was killed and his wife seriously injured after militants broke into his house in Sopore and opened fire.
A police officer and a terrorist died in a shooting and grenade attack in Tinsukia district in the Indian state of Assam.
A bomb explosion in the central Gaza Strip killed at least six people and injured three. Hamas blamed Israel for the attack.
An explosion in a registration center on the electoral lists in eastern Afghanistan, killed at least 17 people and injured 33.
Seven Indians were abducted by armed Talibans militants in the Baghlan province.
Six people were killed, including four government officials and a soldier, in an attack by Boko Haram jihadists on a Chadian army checkpoint on an island in Lake Chad.
A gunman shot and injured Pakistani Interior Minister Ahsan Iqbal while he was visiting his constituency, during a rally in the north-eastern city of Narowal, in Punjab.
Seven Kenyan soldiers were killed after a bomb explosion caused by Al-Shabaab militants in southern Somalia.
Afghan Police shot and killed a suicide bomber who wanted to make a massive attack in Shahr-e-Naw, central Kabul. The blast caused no casualties.
